title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add strawberries with juice, pineapple and nuts.
Put 1/2 mixture in 13 x 9-inch glass dish and refrigerate until firm.
When congealed, spread sour cream over top and pour balance of the gelatin mixture over all and refrigerate again until firm.

title: great grandma's turkey dressing
directions: Break dried bread into squares.
Fry celery and onion with pork and ground heart and liver until meat is done.
Mix with bread.
Add seasonings, milk and beaten eggs.
Stuff into turkey or bake separately at 350° for about an hour.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, dash of pepper and 1/4 cup tomato soup.
Mix well. Shape into 20 small balls and place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining soup, water and Worcestershire together and pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Mix together the eggs, pumpkin, sugar and dry ingredients. Pour batter into a sided 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet, which has been well-greased and lined with waxed paper.
Sprinkle batter with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn cake onto a powdered sugared tea towel.
Peel off waxed paper.
Roll cake and towel and cool in refrigerator at least one hour.
Unroll cake and towel. Spread cake with filling made by beating together until smooth the cream cheese, vanilla, butter and sugar.
Re-roll.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: lemon pepper green beans
directions: Saute beans in butter along with almonds.
Toss with lemon pepper and salt.

title: black forest torte
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Spread batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; bake according to package directions. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack. Slice cake horizontally to make 3 layers. Place bottom layer on cake platter; spread about 1 cup whipped topping and top with 1/3 of cherry pie filling. Repeat process with second and third layers. Chill well.

title: apple cake
directions: Roll batter out and line pan.
Peel apples and place on top of batter. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: golden brownies
directions: Mix in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 or 35 minutes.
Check after 25 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: In 3-quart bowl, place fruit in listed order.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, powdered sugar, butter, eggs and oil. Add flour, soda, cream of tartar, vanilla and salt. Mix well and chill until firm. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: fast peach cheese cake
directions: Combine cake mix and margarine in bowl and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Place peaches over crust.
Mix sour cream and egg yolks.
Spread mixture over peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine dates, boiling water and shortening.
Cover and cool. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat sugar and egg together and add to dates alternately with sifted dry ingredients. Add broken nuts; pour into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Turn onto cake rack to cool.
Flavor improves after standing 24 hours.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium pot, boil water and margarine. Stir in flour and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pot in ball.
Remove from heat.
One at a time, add eggs, mixing well after each.
Separate into small balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 30 to 40 minutes. When cooled, break open and fill with ice cream, pudding, lunch salads, etc.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Put in greased and floured pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: brunch eggs
directions: In a medium bowl, toss together Monterey Jack cheese and flour.
Sprinkle in bottom of 4 qt. baking dish. Brown crumbled sausage and set aside.
Layer mushrooms over cheese.
Top with cheddar cheese, then sausage.
In a bowl, mix eggs and milk until well blended.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Uncover and bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until mixture is puffed and egg custard is set.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 servings.

title: texas wiener relish
directions: Saute onions in oil;
add
ground chuck, brown lightly. Add tomato paste, water
and
tomato sauce.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cover
and
cook
until it thickens. Stir occasionally to avoid sticking.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers; stir.
Put 1/2 of crackers in bottom of large greased casserole dish.
Dump in chicken mix.
Top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Feeds 8 to 10.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, then oil, flour, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add apples and nuts.
Batter will be quite thick.
Bake in a greased and floured 2 x 9 x 12-inch pan for 55 minutes at 350°.
Very good with whipped cream or ice cream while still warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cube it up and cook Stove Top per recipe on box. Put 1/2 dressing in 9 x 9-inch pan.
(Mix cream
of chicken soup with sour cream.)
Put chicken cubes on top of dressing; pour soup mix on top of chicken.
Add rest of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Soak seed in extract and buttermilk.
Set aside.
(Will be bitter if you don't soak.)
Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups of sugar. Add egg yolks and beat.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Butter 8 or 9-inch pan; set aside. Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in 4-quart saucepan; stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full rolling boil. Boil without stirring to soft-ball stage, 234° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla; do not stir. Cool at room temperature to 110° or lukewarm. Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss. Quickly spread into prepared pan; cool. Cut into squares.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with cooked, mashed potatoes and vanilla. Add 10x sugar and salt.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out on wax paper sprinkled with 10x sugar.
Spread peanut butter on this mixture.
Roll up.
Chill and cut into thin slices.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Early in the day, barely cover cabbage with salted water. Cover, boil 7 minutes until tender.
Melt the butter; stir in flour, salt and mustard.
Cook until thickened.
Drain cabbage, reserving 1/2 cup water.
Add liquid and milk to flour mixture. Cook until thickened.
Add cheese; taste for seasoning.
Grease a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Alternate layers of cheese and cabbage. Melt oleo; add to crumbs.
Mix well.
Sprinkle over cabbage. Chill.
Bake 1/2 hour before serving time at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.
Makes 35 squares. This cookie bar tastes more like brownies.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients, using more or less mayonnaise as desired. Use for stuffing celery or for sandwiches.
Yields about 1 1/2 pounds (680 g) pimiento cheese.

title: garden casserole
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon melted butter into a 3-quart casserole to coat surface.
Layer beans, carrots, green pepper, onion, tomatoes, and celery in baking dish.
Combine salt, pepper, sugar and cornstarch; mix well and sprinkle over vegetables.
Dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 10 servings.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Beat all ingredients at low speed for 4 minutes.
Grease and flour a large angel food pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: educated hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1 c. water. Drop by teaspoon into hot grease. Hush puppies will turn over by themselves.

title: colin's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Have baking sheets ready.
Do not grease.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking.
Set to moderate (375°).

title: chicken broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into bite-size pieces and allow to cool completely. Add chicken, grapes and walnuts. Stir in Miracle Whip and chill.
May be served with a meal or on lettuce leaves.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add chopped onions; cook until tender. Stir in milk, soup and cheese.
Add drained corn, cooked noodles and salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beans, in blender.
Mix beans with mixture and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Bacon can be placed on top of beans before baking instead of being added to blender mixture if desired.

title: impossible ham 'n swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease pie plate. Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onions, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture into round meatballs.
Melt shortening in skillet; brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs; keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: south of the border hot salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stew for 2 hours on low heat. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve hot (reheated) or cold.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme, cream cheese and small amount of grated orange rind together.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with ginger. Dippers may be almost any kind of fruit.
Suggestions:
apple slices, orange slices, pink grapefruit slices, pineapple chunks, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: chafing dish meatballs
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients together; form into small balls and fry until done. Drain on paper towels. Cool and freeze.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Place in crock pot on high and cook for 8 hours. Put in jars and seal.

title: philip's vegetable soup
directions: *Three onions, 1 to 2 potatoes, 1 medium turnip, 2 to 3 medium rutabagas, 3 or more ribs of celery (sliced) and 3 or more carrots (sliced) may be used.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, peanut butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Stir well. Stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Place in refrigerator in container or plastic bag until used up.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix shortening and peanut butter.
Beat in sugars and egg until very light and fluffy.
Mix in flour mixture.
Pinch off small pieces of dough, rolling each with palms of hands into roll 2-inches long.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
With tines of fork, press lengthwise.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: aunt ann's pistachio dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: morrison's coconut pie
directions: A luscious pie that takes its name from the rich bottom lands that dot the Mississippi Delta.
This recipe is easy to make if you follow the directions carefully.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in medium bowl. Microwave at High power for 2 to 3 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Spread evenly in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: stuffed peppers and rice
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Cook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Brown hamburger, onion and pepper tops.
Add soup, paste, cooked rice and seasoning.
Stuff peppers.
Arrange in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place strips of cheese on the tops.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 375°.
Freeze remaining filling.

title: empire state baked beans
directions: Wash beans, place in large saucepan with lukewarm water; cover.
Let stand 12 hours.
Do not drain. Add enough cold water to cover the beans well.
Slowly bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 2 hours.
Transfer to greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, covering pork with beans.
Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over beans.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° until beans are soft and a brown crust forms on top and along sides; 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
As the beans dry out, moisten with hot water.
Beans can be reheated successfully.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned brown sugar pie
directions: Make enough biscuit dough to cover bottom of a 9-inch pie pan approximately 1/2-inch thick.
Press out in pan with hands, pressing down slightly in center. Sprinkle over dough the brown sugar.
Dot with the margarine. Add milk.
Bake at 350° until brown. Remove from oven.
Press indentions with fork around over crust allowing brown sugar mixture to soak in crust. Delicious.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix onions and cucumbers with salt and water.
Cover and let set 3 hours before draining.

title: round steak
directions: In heavy-duty foil, place 1/2 onion soup mix on bottom.
Put round steak on top and other package onion soup mix.
Add potatoes and/or carrots.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sherry's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs. add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add chips and nuts.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Take instant pudding, add sour cream, rum, sugar and lime rind. Mix and fold in pineapple and coconut.
Top with whipped cream after refrigerated.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Season and cook hen so you have 2 quarts broth. Saute onion in butter, Strain broth and cook vermicelli in broth. Add cheese and melt. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, peas and salsa. Salt and pepper to taste. Add chicken and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients excluding the cornstarch.
Mix cornstarch with water to make a paste, then add to mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly and roll out as though pastry.
Place on top of pie crust.
Prepare pudding with milk as instructed on package.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: chicken florentine
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch casserole, place ingredients in order listed. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mildred seeley's raisin cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in fruit cocktail and egg.
Pour into greased, 8-inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and chopped nuts and sprinkle over batter.

title: "quick" fluffy biscuits
directions: Note:
The carbonation and "fizz" in the tonic water is responsible for the lightness and extra fluff.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix above ingredients together and serve inside a hollow loaf of French or sourdough bread.

title: fish fillets with mushrooms
directions: Arrange fish fillets in a 13 x 9-inch microwave glass baking dish.
Arrange edges towards outside of dish.
Dot with margarine. Put remaining ingredients over top of fish.
Cook, covered, on High for 5 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: pot de creme
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar and butter in top of double boiler and stir until melted. Add nutmeg and salt. Separate eggs. Beat yolks and add to chocolate mixture. Stir and cook for 2 or 3 minutes over boiling water.
Beat whites until stiff and fold into the chocolate mixture when it has cooled.
Spoon into after dinner coffee cups and place in refrigerator for several hours.
Serve topped with whipped cream and toasted almonds.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix together the ingredients (except the sauce and cottage cheese).
Form the mixture into a pie plate as a crust.
Spread 1 cup cottage cheese over crust and follow with the spaghetti sauce. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and add 1/2 cup grated Mozzarella.
Bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chili corn chowder
directions: Brown ground beef and drain any fat. Saute onions and green pepper. Add all ingredients. Heat to boiling. Then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, covered. Serve with grated cheese on top.

title: oh so good oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Then add eggs and vanilla.
Then sift together and add flour, soda and salt.
Add oats, nuts and raisins and mix well.
Refrigerate. Take spoonfuls and shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: yorkshire puffs
directions: Combine salt and water in saucepan.
Add shortening and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and add flour all at once, stirring vigorously until ball forms.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
(Mixture should be very stiff.)
Brown beef and drain off drippings.
Add beef and thyme to flour mixture, blending thoroughly.
Heat oil to 365°.
Drop puffs by teaspoonfuls into the oil and fry until golden.
Makes about 80.

title: beet jelly
directions: Boil together beef juice, Kool-Aid and Sure-Jell for 2 minutes. Add sugar and boil another 2 minutes.
Put in clean jars and seal.
I cover mine with paraffin. Store in a cool place. Very good!

title: dessert pancakes
directions: Beat eggs well then carefully add flour to avoid lumps.
Add milk and salt.

Use oil or unsalted butter in a heavy frying pan. When pan is hot, pour a small amount of batter to make a paper thin pancake, tilting the hot frying pan in all directions (the batter will spread quickly).
When medium brown do not turn, but remove from pan.
Spread with your favorite jam or applesauce. Roll and dust lightly with powdered sugar.
Serve warm as a dessert.

title: aunt sandy's canned pie filling(apple or blueberry)
directions: Combine tapioca, sugar and juice in 8-quart kettle.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add flavorings; stir in fruit.
Heat just to boiling.
Pack in 7 quart jars 3/4 inch from top.
Hot water bath for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain corn and place in medium-sized bowl. Add flour, sugar, salt, pepper, oil and skim milk and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, blending thoroughly. Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake for an hour or until pudding is set and a little brown on top. Serves 6.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well.
Add applesauce and lemon juice. Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: carob yeast cake
directions: Dissolve
yeast in warm water in small bowl; set aside. Cream oil
and honey.
Add EGG SUBSTITUTE, one tablespoon at a time, beating
well.
Combine carob powder, flour and salt in separate bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition. Stir
in
yeast
mixture
and
vanilla.
Cover
and refrigerate overnight.
Pour batter into 3 greased or sprayed and floured 8-inch
cake
pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and add icing.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip until blended well.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Mix and chill.

title: salsa cruda
directions: Strain first 3 ingredients.
Save spills to put back in.
Chop and mix all together.
Keep in covered jars in the refrigerator.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Mix cream and vanilla and pour over freshly fallen snow in an ice cold bowl.
Add powdered sugar until well blended. Be careful not to let it melt. Add more snow if ice cream is too thin or more sugar if not sweet enough. Eat immediately.

title: pork chop rice casserole
directions: Batter and brown pork chops in oil. Place in casserole dish pour rice over pork chops. Add beef broth and onion soup, sprinkle dry onion soup mix over top of mixture. Cover and bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour.

title: green tomato stew
directions: Brown beef in oil; add chopped onion and shredded chiles and saute 5 minutes.
Add cubed squash, sliced tomatoes and corn cut from cob.
Simmer over low flame for 30 minutes.
Season to taste. Serves 3.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes so they
will be done about an hour ahead of eating time.
Mash while hot, cutting in a stick of margarine or butter.
Add enough milk to give a creamy texture, then blend in well a cup of sour cream for every 10 potatoes.
Spoon into a casserole dish and top with shredded Cheddar.
Cover and set aside on stove.
About 20 minutes before eating, slip casserole dish into oven to melt cheese and re-warm potatoes.

title: crimson fruit punch
directions: Combine punch, juice drink, orange juice and lemonade concentrate; chill. Just before serving, add ginger ale and Chablis or light rum, if desired. Garnish with slices of orange, lemon or lime, if desired.

title: shrimp boil
directions: In large kettle, heat beer and salt to boiling.
Add shrimp; heat just to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Serve with Cocktail Sauce.

title: beef brisket with gravy
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown brisket in oil on both sides over medium-high heat; drain.
Combine hot water and soup mix; pour over brisket.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove brisket to a serving platter.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and cold water until smooth; gradually stir into pan juices.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Thinly slice meat across the grain; serve with the gravy.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add oats, slightly beaten egg, milk and oil.
Stir just to moisten.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12.

title: rice shrimp gumbo
directions: Combine onion, green pepper, 1/4 cup water and bring to boil. Simmer 3 minutes.
Cut up tomatoes and add (juice and all) to the ingredients along with garlic, paprika and pepper.
Add rice, 2 cups water and shrimp.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until rice is cooked.

title: dumpling cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Add chopped nuts and then add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Let cream together until velvety smooth.
Shape into 1-inch squares.
Bake 45 minutes at 280°.
Cool and then roll in powdered sugar.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Form in balls. Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in water; chill.
Fold in rest of ingredients and blend well.
Chill until firm.

title: colonaid icing
directions: Place sugar, water and Karo in saucepan. Boil until mixture spins a thread. Stir and watch (it will boil over). Beat egg whites until stiff (beat with electric mixer). Add syrup in small stream and beat on high speed until it stands in peaks. Add sifted powdered sugar.

title: california scallops(low calorie)
directions: About 50 minutes before serving, let scallops stand in oil and garlic for 30 minutes.
Preheat broiler 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, sprinkle tomato halves with pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
In shallow roasting pan, arrange with scallops.
Over scallops pour margarine, 1/2 teaspoon salt, lemon juice and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Broil about 10 minutes, turning once.
Serve garnished with lemon twists and parsley.

title: southern sweet potato pudding
directions: In a heavy, iron skillet, melt butter.
Mix all other ingredients, adding beaten eggs last.
Pour into hot pan with butter; stir until heated.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in fruit.
Pour half of this mixture into a 9 x 9-inch or 6 x 10-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Keep the rest of the gelatin at room temperature.
Cover set gelatin with sour cream, then with the rest of gelatin.
Chill until set.

title: spinach with yoghurt arab style
directions: Clean, cook and chop spinach.
Squeeze out excess moisture. Cook the onion in ghee or butter for one minute.
Add the cooked spinach and stir to mix.
Warm it through.
Mix the yogurt, garlic and cinnamon in a bowl; add the spinach and onion.
Stir everything together.
Taste and adjust seasoning.
Serve cold.

title: oyster artichoke soup
directions: Melt butter in large soup pot and add flour, stirring to dissolve (but not too brown).
Add water and cook until thick.
Add oysters and all seasonings and simmer about 20 minutes.
Add whipping cream, green onions, parsley and artichoke hearts and cook an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Add wine, if desired, and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve at once.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in butter and then add baking powder, egg and milk.
Save 1/4 cup of mixture.
After butter is cut in, sprinkle this over top of cake. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Prepare vegetables.
Fry bacon until crispy; drain.
Crumble over vegetables; add cheese.
Mix Miracle Whip and sugar.
Pour over salad.
Stir until pieces of vegetables are well coated.

title: spiced pineapple punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice; chill.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Serve over ice.
Yields 3 1/4 quarts.

title: greek salad
directions: In large serving bowl, place lettuce, cucumber, tomatoes, green pepper, scallions, olives and cheese.
Combine olive oil, lemon juice, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic and beat with a fork until well blended.
Pour over salad and mix well.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and dates.
Cook over low heat until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip and remaining ingredients.
Takes several hours for ingredients to freeze firmly.

title: crab chowder(serving size: 10)
directions: Saute onion, garlic and cayenne in margarine over medium heat. Add soup, cream cheese and milk.
Cook and stir until blended. Add corn and crab meat; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sugar.

title: strawberry jello delight
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add frozen strawberries, crushed pineapple (drained) and diced bananas. Pour half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish and let set in refrigerator until firm.
Cover with layer of sour cream, then pour the other 1/2 mixture on top of sour cream.
Refrigerate.
Better if made a day ahead.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Boil vermicelli.
Mix flaked and drained salmon with sauce and stir thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place in medium baking dish in layers with vermicelli.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Uncork a bottle of Grey Riesling and savor with the casserole.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon and onion in butter 5 minutes.
Put ingredients in a pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce to 325° for 20 minutes or until firm.

title: tex mex cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in 6 slices and cook about 10 minutes or until tender, but crisp.
Put into 2-quart greased casserole.
Saute sugar, onion and green pepper in melted butter.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over cabbage and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water for 35 minutes.
Tear off bones and cut in small pieces.
Add soup and sour cream.
Place in buttered casserole and top with 1 cup Town House cracker crumbs. Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over the top.
Sprinkle liberally with poppy seed.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: colin's  favorite clam sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and cook together until bubbly.
Pour over 1/2 pound spaghetti noodles.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a nonstick skillet, add the canola oil and brown onions, celery and green peppers.
Dissolve tomato soup in water; set aside.
Transfer entire skillet mixture to saucepan; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Simmer approximately 1 hour until tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix butter, corn syrup, peanut butter, salt and vanilla.
Sift in powdered sugar gradually.
Knead until well blended.
Add nuts gradually, pressing and kneading into candy.
Press out into 1/2-inch thick square.
Cut into pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: hot taco sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; blend well.
Bring to full boil, then simmer for 30 minutes or until as thick as you like.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix flour, chopped nuts and butter. Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan (have to use your finger). Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Blend well and spread on cooled crust.
Mix puddings and milk.
Beat until thick and pour over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and grated chocolate bar.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.

title: plain pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and mace.
Stir well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: raspberry-applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water. Add partially frozen raspberries; stir until thawed. Stir in applesauce. Pour into 8 x 8-inch dish. Chill until set. Spread sour cream on top.

title: parsley dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add parsley.
Combine beaten egg, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto stew.
Cover closely and cook 15 minutes.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash, onions and carrots until tender.
Drain well.
Add salt and butter.
Line bottom of casserole dish with cornbread crumbs.
Mix vegetables with soup and sour cream.
Pour over crumbs in dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Take out and sprinkle cornbread crumbs on top.
Return to oven and brown.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Put in a large saucepan the margarine or butter, milk and sugar.
Stir constantly until comes to a boil.
Let boil 8 minutes, then pour over mixture in bowl and stir.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: chicken-fruit salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Cool on cutting board and chop into cubes.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: mammaw's ham and beans
directions: Rinse pinto beans.
Remove any stones or old beans.
Soak beans in water overnight in refrigerator.
Drain; add ham bone to beans and cover with water.
Simmer on stove top for 8 hours or cook in slow cooker on low for 15 to 18 hours.
Serve over cornbread.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: sausage rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until rice absorbs liquid.
Serve with French bread topped with garlic butter, Italian seasoning, Mozzarella cheese and broiled to melt cheese.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 1
quart dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour into
melted
margarine.
Do
not stir!
Add peaches, do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in skillet; add small amount of milk to get ingredients stirred.
Gradually add remaining milk.
When gravy begins to thicken, remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring.
Spoon over hot biscuits.
Children love it!

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Chop celery and onion and brown lightly in butter.
Add bread and mix.
Chop tomatoes.
Add bread mixture to tomatoes and mix.
Add sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a 1-quart baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat; add coconut and pecans.
Let cool before frosting cake.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake
at 400° until light brown and set.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: In saucepan in enough boiling, salted water to cover, cook potatoes, onions and carrots, covered, 15 to 20 minutes or until fork-tender.
Meanwhile, open corned beef.
Break it into large chunks.
Place in strainer.
Rest the strainer on top of saucepan. Cover strainer.
Heat about 10 minutes.

title: cheddar dill popovers
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add remaining ingredients (do not overbeat).
Divide into 10 greased muffin cups.
Bake in a 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Decrease temperature to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring butter, cocoa, sugar and milk to boil.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: summer afternoon snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 10 cups.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put cooked chicken, soup, celery, onion, salt, pepper, almonds, lemon juice and mayonnaise in large bowl and mix well. Put a layer of the mixture into a 3-quart casserole.
Add a layer of sliced eggs.
Repeat.
Cover with crushed potato chips and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Cook slowly until done. Add other ingredients. Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: pickle delight
directions: Spread out ham slices and pat dry with paper towels. Spread cream cheese on ham. Place a pickle at one end of ham and roll up. Chill 1/2 hour. Slice into 1/2 to 3/4 inch pieces. Arrange on a serving platter.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken and other ingredients together.
Line a 2-quart casserole dish with one of the pie crusts.
Add fillings.
Put the other pie crust on top.
Cut slits to let air escape.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out; put grated cheese on top and return long enough to melt cheese.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and blend well with mixer. Add oil a little at a time while beating and blend well. STIR in poppy seeds; don't beat. Makes quite a lot; can half if desired, but keeps well in refrigerator.

title: easter wheat pies(italian)
directions: Clean and wash wheat; cover with water to top of large pan and cook until soft.
Rinse in cold water and drain good.
(Shake a few times to remove excess water.)
In large bowl, mix wheat, Ricotta, oil, eggs, cheese, salt, pepper and pepperoni; mix well and let stand 2 to 3 hours to blend flavors.
Taste to see if you need more salt and pepper.

title: mrs. guy empie's raisin bread custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and sugar.
Pour over bread.
Put pan in cold water and bake in slow oven at 325° about 35 minutes.

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Dredge in flour.
Beat with meat mallet.
Brown meat in iron skillet in oil.
Place browned meat in crock-pot.
Add salt, pepper, soup and water.
Set on low.
Let cook all day while you are at work.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together shortening, margarine, sugar and eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in shallow dish.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring 7 cups water and sugar to a boil.
Steep the tea bags in 2 cups boiling water for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix everything together and add 2 cups brandy.
Freeze.
Stir occasionally while in freezer.
To serve, mix with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and canned milk.
Cook until soft ball forms. Take off
stove;
add
peanut
butter,
marshmallow cream and vanilla. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased butter dish.

title: kwanzaa delight
directions: Drain water from tuna and flake tuna into mixing bowl.
Stir in seasonings, onion and mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Fold in raisins, grapes and toasted almonds. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy mushroom rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt. Combine all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese; mix well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Layer with pudding and graham crackers until dish is full.
Top layer is graham crackers.
Melt frosting and pour over top.
Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: microwave beans and rice
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a microwave dish and stir. Set microwave on High for 5 to 10 minutes, then stir.
Set microwave on Low and cook for 1 hour.
(Depending upon the microwave, you may need
to cook longer, until rice is dry.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini and tomatoes.
Dice small amount of onions and peppers.
Layer zucchini, cheese, tomatoes, onions and peppers. Repeat.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake in covered deep Pyrex dish at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until very tender.
Cut open and scoop out potato, leaving 1/8-inch in shell.
Mix or blend remaining ingredients.
Add scooped out potatoes and mix well and spoon back into shell.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, chilies and onion. Spread on seven tortillas. Roll the tortillas. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate. After chilled, remove wax paper and slice each tortilla roll.

title: oven denver omelet
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs and cream until light and fluffy. Stir in the cheese, ham, green pepper and onion. Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking dish. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute vegetables until tender in margarine.
Add mushroom soup and milk and heat thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut green peppers into halves; remove seeds and membrane. Parboil in water to cover in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Saute onion and celery in butter in skillet for 4 to 5 minutes, or until tender.
Add ground beef; cook until ground beef is no longer pink, stirring until crumbly.
Cook rice, using package directions.
Add rice, tomatoes and tomato sauce to ground beef mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Spoon into pepper halves.
Place in baking dish.
Spoon any remaining sauce over peppers.
Bake at 350° until peppers are tender.
Serves 16.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix well the sugar, butter, vanilla and milk; bring to a boil. Beat eggs in mixer real well.
When milk mixture comes to a boil, pour slowly over eggs, beating while pouring into pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes or until crust sets.

title: carolyn's crunchy caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Heat oven to 200°.
Divide corn between 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) ungreased baking pans.
Heat remaining ingredients except baking soda in saucepan.
Stir occasionally, until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in soda until foamy.
Pour on popped corn, stirring until corn is well coated.
Add pecans or peanuts and stir.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Crunchy, delicious snack!

title: swiss chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix ingredients together.
Cook in 3 round pans.
Let cool completely.
Cut in thin layers, making 6 layers.

title: will's spinach salad and hot mushroom dressing
directions: Mix washed spinach with sliced fresh strawberries and slivered almonds.
When ready to serve, pour on dressing.

title: rondeann's quick breakfast ring
directions: Shape biscuits into balls.
Mix together sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll each ball in melted margarine, then roll in sugar-cinnamon-nut mixture.
Arrange balls in bottom of well-greased 8 1/2-inch mold (fluted Bundt pan), leaving about 1/4-inch in between each biscuit.
Make a second layer, placing biscuit balls over spaces.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until done.
Turn out on a plate immediately and decorate with thin powdered sugar frosting and cherries.

title: substitute french fries
directions: Slightly beat egg whites and add seasoning.
Coat potatoes. Lay in single layer on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 450°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: round steak pot roast with mushroom gravy
directions: Cut up the round steak into serving size pieces. Pound the pieces of steak with a meat tenderizing hammer, pounding the steak on both sides.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and add the ingredients.
Mix and pour into a bread pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot ice cream dessert
directions: Toast almonds. Mix vanilla wafers with butter and almonds. Spread 1/2 in dish, then add 1/2 ice cream, softened slightly. Then add 1/2 preserves. Repeat. Can top with whipped cream and more almonds, if desired, but not necessary. Freeze, covered, until ready to serve.

title: television nibbles
directions: Place butter or margarine in shallow baking pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Put pan in oven preheated to 275° until butter melts. Add seasonings to melted butter and mix well.

Add cereals, pretzels sticks and nuts. Stir thoroughly until all are coated. Return pan to oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven and spread mixture on brown paper or paper towels to cool.
Store in screw-top jars to keep fresh and crisp.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni and rinse.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Serve garnished with salad greens.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Place in a large pan the bread and cheese.
Pour over mixture of eggs, milk and salt.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Cook for 10 minutes at 375°, then 45 minutes at 400°.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until, when dropped in cold water, will be brittle.
When syrup quits bubbling, pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add salt, 1 cup chopped nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased platter.
Put pecan halves on top of each piece.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix the ingredients for meatballs together.
Shape into meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drain grease.

title: bertie's coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, buttermilk, sugar and margarine together. Add coconut.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti carbonara madalena
directions: Slice bacon strips into 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute in a large skillet until crisp.
Set aside on a plate.
Squeeze Italian sausage from casing into hot bacon fat and break into small chunks.
Saute about 10 minutes over medium-low heat until cooked through.
Add garlic and saute briefly.
Return bacon to skillet.

title: banana pudding
directions: Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 12 wafers for garnish.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into baking dish.
Add cinnamon and water.
Make a crumble mixture of the sugar and flour and place over the apples.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Drain potatoes well and mash.
Add nutmeg, sugar and butter. Cool.
If too thin, add some crushed cornflakes.
Form into balls around marshmallows.
Dip into beaten egg and roll into crushed cornflakes.
Brown in hot fat.
They cook instantly, so do not burn.
Good cold or hot.
Can be frozen and deep fry later.

title: chicken curry and green rice
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Saute onion and curry; blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook on low until thick and bubbly, as for white sauce.
Remove from heat; stir in broth and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Add chicken and lemon juice.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serves 8.

title: au gratin beef bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, onion, celery and green pepper until meat is no longer pink and vegetables are tender; drain. In a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish, combine beef mixture, potatoes with contents of sauce mix, soup and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in the water and milk. Bake, uncovered, at 350° to 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in bowl; beat until well mixed.
Add 1/4 of the chopped beef and blend.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining beef.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine sugar, flour and water.
Pour batter into baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick spray coating.
Place fresh berries on top, then drizzle melted margarine over the fruit. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Batter rises on top and makes a nice topping for cobbler.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: jewish chicken soup(penicillin)
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add chicken, peeled carrots, whole celery, whole onion, garlic, dill, parsnips, salt and pepper. Simmer 2 hours until chicken falls from bone.
Cool.
Remove vegetables and chicken from liquid.
Pour liquid through strainer to clear broth.
(May be done twice.)
Place in fridge to solidify fat and skim from top.
Carrots, celery and onion may be sliced and added to soup or pureed for creamier mixture.
Remove chicken from bone.
Cut into pieces and add to broth.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Drain potatoes, reserving 1 cup liquid (add water to equal 1 cup liquid, if necessary).
Set potato water aside. Mash potatoes.
Measure 1 cup mashed potatoes; set aside.

title: don't know cake
directions: First Layer:
Combine butter and 2 eggs to cake mix; spread in cake pan.

title: dean smith's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick. Pour into baked pie shell. Cool while beating egg whites for meringue. Top with meringue and heat in the oven until golden brown at 325 degrees.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic, then add sour cream.
Combine mixture and green beans in a casserole dish.
Cover with cheese, grated.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Place eggs in a small bowl. Gradually add chocolate mixture to eggs, stirring constantly.
Return mixture to saucepan; cook and stir over low heat for about 7 minutes. Cool slightly; add nuts. Fold in marshmallows.
Line two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans with plastic wrap.
Press mixture into pans.
Refrigerate.
When molded, remove from pan and dust with sugar. Cut into 1-inch squares.
Candy freezes well.
Serve frozen or at room temperature.

title: peanut kisses
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Sift together flour, soda, salt and set aside. Cream butter and peanut butter together and add sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and roll in small balls. Roll in sugar, place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 minutes and remove from oven. Place a Hershey's Kiss on each firmly. Return to oven 3 minutes. Makes about 24 to 36 cookies.

title: fresh sausage patties
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Brown patties on both sides over medium heat, about 15 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix and let cool the strawberry jello, boiling water and sugar. Mix orange juice, pineapple juice, cold water and lemon juice.
Add to strawberry ingredients and freeze.
Serve with ginger ale and pineapple sherbet.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour apples into pan.
Squeeze small amount of lemon juice over apples. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon and sprinkle cake mix over apples.
Add more cinnamon and add walnuts on top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake for 1 hour and serve hot, plain or with ice cream of whipped cream.

title: lemon poppyseed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Lightly grease bundt or loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. It makes (1) loaf.
Cool completely, remove from pan and drizzle with citrus glaze.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Separate from bone and cut into small pieces. Mix it with sour cream, mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Brown onion with margarine.
Mix with dressing mix and water.
Combine chicken mixture and dressing.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: oven baked steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from meat.
Cut meat into 6 serving pieces.
In plastic bag, combine half of flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Shake meat into flour mixture to coat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off of fruit and add water to make 3 cups liquid. Bring liquid to boil and cook 1 small package vanilla pudding and 1 small package tapioca pudding.
Add about 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Add pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Chill.

title: cream fruit pie
directions: *Three kiwis (sliced and peeled), 1 cup blueberries and 1/2 cup grapes, strawberries or peaches.
Or 1 can cherry pie filling.

title: smoked eel stew
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a heavy-duty 6-quart pot over high heat.
Simmer 40 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Skim off the excess fat.
Serve hot with plenty of bread.
Serves 6.

title: pig lickin' good
directions: Mix by hand the eggs and oil.
Add oranges and juice.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take out and let cool.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix altogether and add Miracle Whip to taste.
Chill.

title: cheese olive puffs
directions: Mix flour, margarine and cheese well (like pie crust dough) and chill well.
Pat out small portion of dough in your hand. Wrap around an olive.
Place wrapped olives on a cookie sheet and freeze. Store in freezer bag.
To bake, place on cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.
Recipe may be doubled easily.

title: apple squares - passover
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add yolks, oil and lemon juice and rind. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread 1/2 of the batter in the pan.
Cover with apple slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Cover with rest of the batter.
(Optional: You may sprinkle with more cinnamon-sugar mixture at this time.)
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes in an 8-inch greased square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quick meat stew
directions: Brown meat in margarine and flour.
Add soup. Cook until thickened.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: You may substitute 1 teaspoon banana or black walnut flavoring and 1/2 cup nuts for poppy seed.

title: all vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together carrots, green beans, diced celery, diced onions, diced green peppers, mushroom bits and pieces, tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle tapioca over top to blend in. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: green and white vegetable salad
directions: Remove large leaves of broccoli.
Cut off tough ends of stalks; discard.
Cut up pieces of celery, cauliflower and onions. Blend mayonnaise, cream, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture over vegetables.
Cover and chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef and peppers in crock-pot
directions: Cut the steak into serving size pieces.
If desired you can brown the meat in a little hot oil before adding to crock-pot. Place the peppers in bottom of crockpot, reserving a few to place on top of meat, if desired.
Add vegetables and then meat.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat and peppers.
Cover and cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.
Yield: 8 servings. Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 34 g, fat 14 g, calories 237.

title: nonfat sweetened condensed milk
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure or bowl, mix dry milk and water until smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds, until heated but not boiling. Makes 1 1/3 cups, equal to 1 (14 ounce) can.
Contains 219 calories.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt butter; add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until light brown.
Add all other ingredients (spaghetti, cooked, is added last) except cheese.
Cook down until thick.
Put in baking dish; top with cheese and put in oven to melt.

title: calico salad
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots and peas.
Add pimientos, onion and parsley.
Add French dressing.
Chill 1 hour.
Add lettuce, broken in bite size pieces.
Toss lightly.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add margarine; mix well.
Mix Parmesan cheese and eggs together.
Blend with spaghetti and margarine.
Spread into a pie dish.
Spread cottage cheese on top of spaghetti, add browned ground beef and Ragu sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Put back into oven to melt cheese.

title: corned beef brisket
directions: Place corned beef brisket in a 3-quart covered baking dish. Mix cream of mushroom soup and soup mix; add to baking dish.
Bake until tender at 400°.
Makes its own gravy.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add syrup, cocoa, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes or until soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from heat.
Beat immediately.
When it begins to lose its gloss, pour onto wax paper or a plate.
Cut when cool.

title: sausage ragout
directions: Cut sausages into 1/2-inch slices.
Heat olive oil in a skillet and add sausage pieces.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sausage pieces are well browned.
Add onion and garlic; cook for another 5 minutes.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at
a time,
mixing after each.
Add extracts.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: poppy seed zucchini bread
directions: Beat the wet ingredients.
Stir in zucchini.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces.
Add sliced onion, cheese and bacon.

title: pineapple cake filling
directions: In a saucepan, combine all the ingredients.
Cook and stir until thick.
Cool.
Spread on 2 layers of cake.
Use yellow or white cake mixes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Cover tea bags with boiling water and let steep for 10 minutes.
Simmer together the pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and cinnamon sticks.
Add tea and serve hot.

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Make several days ahead in double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Melt chocolate pieces.
Stir in peanuts and noodles until they are well coated with chocolate.
Drop by heaping teaspoons onto wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Top each with a 1/4 candied cherry.
Refrigerate until served.
If they soften when served, refrigerate again until firm.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: shrimp and walnut fettucine
directions: While the noodles cook, you can quickly make the creamy sauce.

title: azuki shortbread
directions: Cream softened margarine with sugar.
Add salt to flour. Alternately add flour mixture and condensed milk to creamed margarine until well blended.
Put 1/2 of dough into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Flatten to cover bottom of pan.
Spread Koshian or Tsubushian to cover dough.
Add rest of dough and spread to cover the red beans.
Brush top with beaten egg white.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour until lightly brown.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch rectangles when done.
Cool in pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a loaf pan.
Put extra ketchup, onion and Heinz 57 on top.
Put a little water around edges of meat loaf to retain moistness during baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: crab cakes
directions: Fry celery, onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add crab, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well; form into cakes.
Dip cakes in cracker crumbs, then egg, then cracker crumbs and fry slowly.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Melt shortening and allow to cool.
Dissolve 1 1/2 or 2 packages yeast in cup with a little lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make like a cake dough (about 5 cups) and let rise for 2 hours.

Add more flour (about 3 cups plus a little) with 1 tablespoon salt, 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon soda. Mix thoroughly to handling consistency and place in refrigerator. Cover with wax paper and damp cloth.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 85 to 100.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well: mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Toss together with the remaining ingredients when ready to serve.
One cup of sunflower seeds are also good if you like them.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with a tablespoon or so of sour cream. Mix in the rest of the ingredients and heat at 325° until heated through.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: old fashion cabbage salad
directions: Cook all ingredients and pour over chopped cabbage when cool.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Coat with pecans. Serve with crackers.
Can be sealed in airtight container and refrigerate ahead.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: three meat casserole
directions: Cook, crumble and reserve grease from bacon.
Dice onion and cook in bacon grease.
Cook macaroni until tender and set aside. Cube ham and chicken and set aside.
Combine all ingredients and add enough milk to make extra moist.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar-coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water (medium heat); stir frequently. Add peanuts;
cook and stir until peanuts are coated and there is no more
liquid.
Put	peanuts
on
ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 30 minutes at 300°; stir every 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients (except nuts) in a bowl and mix.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick pecan drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: hidden valley ranch chicken breasts
directions: Whisk juice and dressing together.
Marinate chicken in mixture for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake breasts in juice at 350° for 45 minutes (depends on thickness of meat).
Remove breasts from pan. Thicken sauce with cornstarch on stove top or in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with baked potato or rice.
It's a favorite!

title: chicken neopolitan
directions: Fry chicken in hot oil until cooked, about 5 minutes.
Discard all grease and add garlic and parsley.
Return to heat and stir to pick up flavors.
Remove from heat and add your mushrooms and spices.
Add butter and break into 4 or 5 pieces.
Return to medium heat, stirring until butter is melted and hot.
If butter separates, take off heat and add 1 teaspoon of water and cream all together again.
This dish goes great with a side of linguini and a nice tomato salad.
Serves 2.
Enjoy!

title: cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread slices and place, buttered side down, in a baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Spread with grated cheese.
Add another layer of bread, buttered side up.
Cover with remaining cheese.

title: the best carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding carrots and nuts last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook ground chuck and drain.
Add other ingredients and cook on high in crock-pot for 30 minutes; turn to low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: do-over doughnuts
directions: Cut doughnuts in half, leaving in circles.
Spread with butter.
Broil until golden brown.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in honey and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together, then add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Combine lemonade
and condensed milk in bowl;
mix well (do not
use
electric
mixer).
Fold
in the whipped topping. When smooth, put into crust and chill until set, approximately 2 to 3 hours.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Season and brown the chicken in a Dutch oven or deep skillet. Remove chicken and some of the fat.
Bone chicken.
Stir flour into remaining fat.
Add the soup, milk, evaporated milk and celery seed.
Stir until mixed.
Return chicken to pan and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: mosquito repellent
directions: Mix together, add 10 gallons of water.	Spray entire lawn and any bushes.
Kills mosquito eggs.
Repeat one week later.

title: spring asparagus
directions: Blend together soup, cheese, 1/4 teaspoon marjoram and asparagus liquid.
Carefully mix in asparagus and eggs.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Combine butter or oleo and 1/8 teaspoon marjoram.
Add cereal crumbs.
Stir to coat evenly.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brazilian pot roast
directions: Cut slit through center of steak, 3 to 4-inches long.
Enlarge pocket to about 1-inch from all edges of meat.
Rub inside with 1 teaspoon salt.
Coarsely chop olives.
Heat oil.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic and cook until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes, olives, chili powder and salt.
Cover and cook gently for 5 minutes.
Mix rice with 1 1/4 cups tomato sauce.
Spoon into pocket of meat and skewer shut.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Add to remaining tomato sauce.
Add meat to bacon fat and brown well.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1/2 cup water and add to meat.
Cover and cook slowly 1 hour.
Remove cover and spoon on rest of tomato sauce.
Cover and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order; mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch glass pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: one-pot tuna pasta
directions: Bring water, bouillon cubes, pepper and basil leaves to a boil in a 4-quart pot. Gradually add pasta so that water continues to boil. Cover and simmer for 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and continue to beat until light.
Add vanilla and sifted flour and mix well.
Fold in chopped walnuts. Shape into balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.

title: country-style pancakes
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Beat egg; add milk and shortening and blend into flour mixture.
Drop batter on hot griddle.
Turn pancakes when bubbles appear.
Makes 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: cherry supreme delight
directions: Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar. Beat until completely smooth. Pour into butter crust. Smooth out top.	Add one can cherry pie filling to top.	Place in refrigerator to chill and set up.

title: easy lemonade pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients. Pour into pie crust. Chill 2 hours before serving. Top with whip topping, if desired.

title: cherry nut pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar until creamy; beat 10 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring and blend well.
Alternate flour with milk.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in cherries.
Pour into large greased tube pan.
Put in cold oven; set oven at 275°.
Bake for 2 hours and 10 minutes.
Cool, then frost (recipe follows).

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Fry meat and onion in butter until brown.
Add salt, pepper, celery and water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add bean sprouts. Blend cornstarch with 2 tablespoons of water and add soy sauce and sugar.
Stir into meat-vegetable mixture and heat until thickened.
Add mushrooms and serve over chow mein noodles.

title: christmas salad
directions: Melt milk and marshmallows in double boiler.
Fix 1 package of lime

title: barbecue
directions: Wash roast and pat dry with paper towel.
Place roast in crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover and cook until done (4 to 5 hours).
Cool slightly and shred with fork.

title: frosty pineapple pie
directions: Bake pie shells until light brown.
Set aside to cool.
Chill can of Carnation until almost frozen.
Bring to a boil pineapple, sugar and Jell-O.
Place in refrigerator to chill as you did milk. Whip iced Carnation with lemon juice until it stands and peaks. Then combine cold Jell-O mixture in large bowl.
Pour into pie shells and immediately place in freezer.
Serve directly from freezer.
Do not thaw more than 10 minutes.
Will keep as long as frozen.

title: scalloped corn with broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/4 cup cracker crumbs, 1 tablespoon butter, salt and pepper and put in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Mix remaining cracker crumbs with 1 tablespoon butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crumble topping for ice cream
directions: Combine oats, sugar, flour, salt and pecans.
Add butter and mix well with pastry blender.
Spread into a thin layer on a baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned, about 12 minutes.
Break up with a fork.
Remove from pan and cool.
Dip ice cream cones into crumble or sprinkle over ice cream sundaes. Makes 3 1/2 cups of crumble.

title: chocolate medallion cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and shortening together; add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Sift flour and salt together; set aside.
Make a smooth paste of the cocoa and boiling water; cool slightly.
Stir baking soda into buttermilk and add alternately with sifted flour to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add cocoa-water mixture and blend well.
Blend in vanilla.
Bake 15 minutes in cupcake tins.

title: classic scrambled eggs
directions: In a medium bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Gradually blend in eggs and pepper.
In a 10-inch skillet over low heat, melt margarine.
Pour in egg mixture.
Add eggs begin to set, stir lightly so uncooked egg flows to bottom.
Cook until set but still very moist.
Garnish with parsley or chives.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: hi ho cracker applesauce pie
directions: Use an oval shaped oven-safe baking dish; butter both sides and bottom.
Add spice to applesauce and mix well.
In dish, alternate layers of crackers and applesauce, ending with applesauce.
On each layer, put slivers of margarine and sprinkle lightly with sugar.
When all layers are complete, add topping.

title: stack cake
directions: Heat.
Pour over cake while warm.
Let run down sides.

title: orange breakfast ring
directions: Combine sugar and orange rind. Separate biscuits. Dip each in butter and coat with sugar mixture. Stand biscuits on sides, overlapping edges in a 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Remove ring from pan and invert on serving tray. Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar, mixing until smooth. Add orange juice and stir well. Spoon mixture over top while ring is hot. Serve warm.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Spread toast with butter and cut each slice in 4 pieces. Alternate layers of bread and cheese in greased baking dish, ending top layer with cheese.
Combine milk, eggs and seasonings to pour over bread and cheese.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place
butter
in
a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place in oven to melt. Remove pan. Sprinkle coconut over crumbs. Add layer of
chips
and pecans.
Pour condensed milk over top. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.	Cut. Makes 30 bars.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix together. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: peggy's fruit cake
directions: Mix milk, marshmallows and margarine together (melt in microwave).
Mix all other ingredients well and pour milk mixture over.
Crush crackers; put half in mixture and roll batter in other half of crumbs.
Freezes very well.
Keeps in refrigerator.

title: old-fashion kraut
directions: Wash and shred cabbage.
Place in stone crock jar.
Add about a snuff glass full of salt.
Mix well.
This will make a brine.
Push cabbage down so brine will cover it; weight it down with a plate.
Cover.
Leave 9 days.
Take out of jar and heat kraut and bring to a boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: chicken livers superbe
directions: Saute livers in 3 tablespoons of butter until brown (about 5 minutes).
Remove from skillet.
Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add mushrooms and saute lightly.
Stir in wine, water, parsley, flour, bouillon cube, mustard and rosemary until blended. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until sauce thickens.
Return livers to skillet and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve with hot, fluffy rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix and mash together.
Set in refrigerator until firm.
Mix about 1/4 cup chopped pecans and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Roll tuna ball in pecan mixture.
Great served with Triscuits crackers.
May use deviled ham, Spam (ground).
Just omit liquid smoke and if desired, lemon juice, also.

title: different and delicious salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in the hot water.
While still hot, add Jell-O.
Cool and add applesauce.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in pan. Set until solid.
Mix cheese, cream and mayonnaise and spread over solid mixture.
Add remaining Jell-O and chill.

title: english fruit teabread
directions: Put the dried fruit and sugar in a bowl.
Pour the tea over; soak overnight.
Grease and base-line a 2-pint loaf tin.
The next day, add the egg, flour, baking powder and mixed spice to the fruit and tea mixture.
Beat thoroughly with a wooden spoon until all ingredients are evenly combined.
Spoon into the prepared tin; level the surface.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours, or until well risen and a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Turn out onto a wire rack to cool.
Serve sliced and spread with butter.
Serves 14.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Pre-heat your oven to 425 degrees.
Cut the chicken breasts into bite size pieces.
Spray a 9x13 inch casserole dish with cooking spray and then put the chicken in to the dish.
Salt and pepper the chicken.

Put the slices of Swiss cheese on top of the chicken pieces and make sure that the cheese covers the chicken. Cover the top of the Swiss cheese with the cream of chicken soup and then spread the stuffing mix on top of the soup.
Cover the dish with tinfoil and bake in the oven for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
The dish should be bubbly when removed from the oven.
Serve hot with any vegetables of your choice.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spoon heaping tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: salsa dip sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in your gourmet chopper and mix to consistency desired.
The gourmet chopper makes a finer cut.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Top each chicken breast with a slice of Swiss cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and put in pan; form crust.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix as a cake and add nuts last.
Put into 2 bread pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: thanksgiving dinner
directions: Get up early on Thanksgiving Day and travel to the location of the dinner.
(If the visit requires an overnight stay, be sure to pack.)
Upon arriving at your destination, be prepared for luscious, mouth-watering smells.
Help with any preparations or stay out of the way.
Sit down at the table, say grace and enjoy, enjoy, enjoy! It is always a good idea to help with the clean up!

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with eggnog, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in coconut and flavorings.
Pour batter into a floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Mix well; do not stir more than two minutes.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: candy apples
directions: Use a large pot.
Mix sugar, coloring and syrup with water; enough water to dissolve sugar.
Use thermometer.
Let candy cook until thermometer reaches 275°.
Using skewers or sticks, dip apples into candy on low heat.
Use margarine on tabletop or countertop.
Place apples down with skewers up, let them cool. Wrap with wax paper or Saran Wrap.

title: pork green chili
directions: Brown pork over
medium
heat,	adding	garlic salt and white pepper while stirring.
Put
in a 1 1/2 to 2 gallon pot. Add tomatoes, jalapenos, onion and 1/2 gallon water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer
for
hours.
Add
salt
and
pepper to taste.
Add pinto
beans.
Refrigerate	overnight to allow the oil to float to the top.
Remove oil, heat and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels, crumble and set aside. Cut the broccoli into pieces.
Cook until crisp-tender.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion.
In a small bowl, stir together salad dressing, sugar and vinegar until well blended. Spoon over broccoli mixture.
Toss to coat. Sprinkle bacon over salad and toss.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt 1
stick of margarine in a 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Add layer of cornmeal dressing mix, layer of chicken, 1 can cream of chicken soup mixed with 1 can chicken broth.
Repeat.
Top with dressing mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pittsburg potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease casserole.
Cook the potatoes; cool and peel.
Grate on large side of grater.
Grate onion and cheese.
Mix potatoes, onion, cheese and melted margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1/2 hour.

title: chow chow
directions: A food processor is a good thing to use to chop the vegetables.
Mix together with salt and let soak overnight.
Next, morning, drain well.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar, mustard seeds, and turmeric.
Add vegetables and bring to boil.
Let boil 3 minutes and seal in sterilized jars.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread cream cheese over a radius of about 6 to 8-inches across.
Cover with crabmeat and then with cocktail sauce.
Use any flavor of cracker.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes into 4-cup buttered casserole.
Add half the bread crumbs and mix.
Stir in onion salt and sugar.
Brown rest of bread crumbs in the butter and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Place in 375° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until hot through.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cream cheese crescents(hungarian kifli)
directions: *You must mix dough thoroughly to make a nice Kifli.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as per directions.
Drain and cool under running water.
Drain again.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Best if refrigerated at least 8 hours.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Tear bread into small pieces in a large bowl.
Let stand overnight.
Saute onion and celery in margarine in skillet until tender.
Add parsley and mushrooms; mix well.
Spoon over bread. Stir in poultry seasoning, salt and sage.
Add broth; mix well. Stir in eggs.
Spoon into 5-quart slow cooker or crock-pot.
Cook, covered, on High for 1 hour.
Cook on low for 5 hours.
Do not stir.
Dressing will puff up.

title: alan dimisko's clam dip
directions: Put the clams and lemon juice in frying pan at medium heat for 15 minutes.
While that is cooking, in another pan, cook onion, garlic, green pepper, butter, parsley and spices until onions and green pepper are cooked.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except for the cheese.
Put everything in a baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; serve with crackers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients; mix by hand. Add some strawberry juice.
Blend in strawberries and nuts.
Pour in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour together in a large bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Remove 1 cup to be used as topping.
Place remainder in 8 x 8-inch pan and press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth with sugar.
Beat in egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour this onto baked crust and top with reserved mix.
Return to 350° oven and bake 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: rigatono portofino
directions: Prepare rigatoni and set aside.
Roast a red pepper, then peel, seed and slice into 1-inch long julienne strips.
Place in bowl along with olives, Prosciutto, nuts and thyme.
Toss to combine.
Bring a large pot of water to boil and cook pasta until al dente.
Drain; place in serving bowl and toss with olive oil and juice of lemon.
