Add pepper/olive mixture and toss.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: pecan carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare two nine-inch pans.
Sift dry ingredients twice.
Blend in oil and eggs.
Beat 4 minutes.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Pour in prepared pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 easy party punch
directions: Combine concentrate and syrup; add ginger ale.
Pour over ice in small punch bowl.
Garnish with orange slices and strawberries, if desired.
Makes 10 (4 ounce) servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Pour boiling water over soda and raisins.
Let stand.

title: burnt cremes
directions: Heat cream over low heat until bubbles form around edges. Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick.
Beating constantly, pour in cream and vanilla.
Pour mixture into porridges.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When done and cool, sprinkle with sugar and place under broiler until medium brown.

title: colin's favorite meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Shape into one loaf or two smaller loaves.
Place in a baking dish or loaf pan and cover with 1/2 cup tomato sauce and 1/2 cup ketchup (combined). Bake, covered, at 350° for about an hour.
During the last 15 minutes of baking, take the cover off.
Serves 6.

title: special iced tea
directions: Heat 1 cup water to boiling in microwave.
Add sugar and stir to completely dissolve. In large pitcher, add sugar, water, tea mix and thawed lemonade.
Add remaining water.
Keep refrigerated. Serve over ice cubes.
Makes 1 3/4 quarts.

title: breakfast biscuits(makes 12 biscuits)
directions: Grease an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut butter into flour mixture until it forms crumbs.
Use eggbeater to beat in the eggs and cream.
Knead and turn out onto a floured cutting board.
Cut biscuits and place on the greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: honey lemon chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour mixture.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and coat pieces of chicken with flour well.
Bake 45 minutes.
Glaze with honey lemon mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon herb dressing(low-fat dressing)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Toss gently until well blended. Store in airtight container in a cool, dry place for up to 6 months.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: In a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half of dry bread crumbs.
Combine applesauce, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Spread applesauce mixture over bread crumbs.
Layer remaining bread crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour over bread mixture.
Lightly sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: christmas morning souffle
directions: Trim crusts and cut bread in cubes.
Put layer of bread in a large, buttered casserole or souffle dish.
Cover bread with cheese, then cover cheese with remaining bread.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and seasonings to eggs.
Pour over bread.
Pour melted butter over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Great for baking while opening Christmas presents; when you are done with opening your gifts, your breakfast is done.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until almost done; drain.
Put carrots into frying pan and add margarine and brown sugar.
In separate small bowl, mix water and cornstarch until smooth and add to carrot mixture.
Let it simmer uncovered on stove for 30 minutes; add nuts.
Put carrots into a casserole dish and keep warm in oven (very low temperature) indefinitely.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw the potatoes.
Mix 1/2 stick of butter with corn flakes and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together and put in baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle the cornflake-butter mixture on top. Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: spicy sausage and potatoes in a skillet
directions: In 10-inch (25 cm.) skillet, combine sausage, potatoes, pepper and thyme.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are browned (10 to 12 minutes).
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover; cook until potatoes are tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Continue cooking, uncovered, until vegetables are crispy tender (4 to 5 minutes).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add macaroni and pizza sauce.
Top with mushrooms, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is slightly brown.

title: thai spiced baked fish
directions: Prepare Thai spice mix according to package directions.
Pour over fish; bake about 20 minutes.
Simple; spicy; superb!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil Carnation milk, sugar, butter or margarine and salt to soft ball stage.
Set off heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla, marshmallow cream and pecans.
Stir until smooth.
Add plain flour; stir in well and pour into buttered pans.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Crush potato chips and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: berry compote
directions: In a large saucepan, combine fruit, sugar, lemon juice, water and vanilla bean.
Gently stir over very low heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and cool.
Discard vanilla bean. Pour fruit into a glass serving bowl and chill.
Serve with cookies, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: big hamburger casserole
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or more.

title: ohio grange cookbook chili
directions: Brown beef, onions, garlic and spices (except salt) together until beef is no longer pink.
Add tomatoes, water and salt; bring to a boil and cook 1 hour on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans; simmer another hour.
Serve with corn bread or saltines.

title: the bishop
directions: Stud orange with cloves and simmer with wine and cinnamon stick in medium saucepan 30 minutes. Add sugar and stir until dissolved. Serve in preheated mugs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rum custard cake
directions: Combine yolks and sugar in medium saucepan.
Gradually add cornstarch and vanilla.
Add hot milk, whisking constantly.
Cook over very low heat or in double boiler, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy dill sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Serve with burgers, beef or lamb.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: egg salad triangles
directions: Combine eggs, olives and green onions; stir in salad dressing and mustard.
Spread each slice of bread with about 1/4 cup of egg mixture.
Cut each slice of bread diagonally into quarters.
If desired, garnish each with slice of olive.
Makes 20 sandwiches.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour 2 cups batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in heavy saucepan over low heat, melt caramels and margarine.
Remove from heat; add sweetened condensed milk. Mix well.
Spread caramel mixture over cake; spread remaining cake batter over caramel mixture.
Top with nuts.
Return to oven; bake 30 to 35 minutes longer or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.
Serve with dollop of whipped cream.

title: fresh and frosty lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice and sugar.
Add water, stirring.
Serve over ice in glasses and garnish with lemon slices.
May add grenadine for pink lemonade.

title: imagination cake
directions: Mix cake mix with dry lemon or orange flavored gelatin in a large bowl, then add all the other ingredients at once.
Mix with an electric beater for 2 minutes.
This is a thin batter.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream together cream cheese and eggs; stir in remaining ingredients, except soup.
Let sit to thicken.
Form balls with a mixture about the size of walnuts.
Brown in skillet, turning often.
To warm, simmer in mushroom soup.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Partly thaw frozen dough.
Cut into 32 pieces (about walnut size).
Lay pieces in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with butterscotch pudding.
Melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon. Stir together and pour over dough.
Let rise for 10 to 12 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut vegetables in small to medium pieces.
Mix everything in a large saucepan.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes, reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until veggies are tender.

title: raspberry jello whip
directions: Stir jello into boiling water; add frozen raspberries and stir until mixed well.
Chill.
Make Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold into jello mixture when it has begun to set.

title: cherry delighteverton, missouri
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: hello dollies!
directions: Put butter in 5 x 6-inch pan and melt.
Pour crumbs in pan; even out and pack.
Pour 3/4 of Eagle Brand in pan.
Cover pan with chocolate, then chocolate chips, then nuts and then add rest of milk.
Bake at 325° until brown, about 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add cinnamon and allspice.
Add flour and apples alternately, beating slowly until well mixed.
Stir in raisins and 1 cup chopped nuts. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into 2 or 3 "sausages."
Roll long cookie dough sausages into waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice in 1/4-inch cookies and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (until lightly browned).
Cool slightly.
Roll in cinnamon/sugar mixture.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs.
Add mashed potatoes, milk, water and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients.
Roll on floured surface and cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep fry in vegetable oil or shortening until golden brown.
Coat with sugar, cinnamon, powdered sugar or frosting.

title: "skordalia" garlic sauce
directions: Boil potatoes in 3 cups water for about 1/2 hour or until tender.
Peel and cut into quarters.
Place 1/4 cup water in blender with garlic cloves and pulverize for 20 seconds.
Add 1 potato, salt, 1 tablespoon olive oil and 1 tablespoon vinegar and blend for 30 seconds.
Add remaining potato, oil and vinegar and blend evenly for 30 to 45 seconds until all ingredients are smooth (the consistency will resemble that of pancake batter).
Place in a bowl; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
It will thicken to a spread-like consistency for serving.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: shrimp creole(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, melt shortening at High for 1 to 2 minutes; blend in flour.
Add onions, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Microwave at High for 3 to 4 1/2 minutes or until onion is transparent; stir in tomato paste until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.

Cover and microwave at Medium 20 to 25 minutes or until sauce is thick and bubbly, stirring once or twice. Stir in shrimp; cover and microwave at 50% Medium 3 1/2 to 7 1/2 minutes or until shrimp is opaque, stirring once or twice.
Do not overcook.
Let stand, covered, 3 to 5 minutes.
This dish is best made in advance and reheated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: better butter
directions: Heat and stir.
Cool and store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: casserole of hot fruit salad
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Stir in oranges, pineapple and bread cubes.
Turn into a greased 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: aunt nora's date cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and cinnamon together.
Pour hot water over dates; add soda and let cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat.
Add dates.
Mix flour and nuts.
Add to mixture and beat.
I usually double the recipe and it provides enough batter for three oiled loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
My favorite Christmas baking.

title: nut gems
directions: Sift flour, measure; sift again.
Cream butter and sugar and cream until smooth.
Blend in flour; stir in nuts, water and rum flavor.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and bake in ungreased pans at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter and cream and let boil one minute. Then add rest of ingredients.
Finally spoon onto wax paper and let them get hard.

title: rice dish
directions: Boil rice in water. In casserole dish, divide rice in 3 parts. Add slices of cheese to each layer.
Beat eggs.
Pour over rice. Add enough milk to cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: tomato meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except 3 Tbsp. ketchup.
Place in greased load pan 7 1/2x3 1/2x 2 1/2.
Put remaining 3 Tbsp. ketchup on top.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 375° May use lamb or veal.

title: fudgy chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine; remove from heat.
In a large mixer bowl, combine condensed milk and warm chocolate mixture; mix well. Stir in eggs, hot water, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Top with pecans and coconut.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until coconut is lightly browned.
Serve warm or chilled. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna to package directions; drain.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
In a 15 x 9-inch baking dish, layer sauce, lasagna and then more sauce.
Then all the spinach mixture, half the remaining Mozzarella cheese, then a layer of lasagna and sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and top with the remaining Mozzarella cheese and parsley. Bake 15 minutes and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix
the flour and margarine real well in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Then, mix in pecans and press down in pan until it looks like cookie
dough.
Bake
approximately
25 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: blueberry yum-yum cake
directions: Mix, folding Cool Whip in last.
Spread topping over cake making a raised edge around outside.
Pour 1 can blueberry pie filling evenly over top.
Chill and serve.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat together soup, sour cream and salsa.
Place chicken, cheese, onions and 2 tablespoons of heated sauce in tortilla; roll and repeat.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with rest of cheese and sauce.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brandied fruit starter
directions: Obtain eight cups apothecary jar with lose fitting lid. Drain fruit well.
Put above ingredients in jar and stir with plastic spoon.
Put top on jar and allow to ferment on your range top or in a warm place for two weeks.
Stir once every day.
Be sure to use only plastic spoon.
After seven days it is ready to use, but do not add more fruit for two weeks.
Never let the contents of the jar get below 3 cups or the process will stop.

title: fruit soup(sotsuppe)
directions: Wash fruit and soak 1 hour or longer in water to cover (about 2 quarts).
Add cinnamon and sugar; cook until fruit is almost done.
Add tapioca and cook until clear.
Remove from stove.
Add grape juice, orange and lemon.
This can be varied by adding other fruit.
If soup is too thick, add more fruit juice.
Serve either hot as soup or cold as dessert.

title: famous meat loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine steak, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, water and onion soup mix.
Mix well until blended.
Pack mixture into a 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover with bacon strips.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: empanadas
directions: Mix flour and Crisco; add your sugar and salt.
Mix in Coke and work dough with hands.
Make little balls and roll out with a rolling pin like a small tortilla.
Fill with pumpkin.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Lower heat to simmer.
Add catsup; heat until bubbling.
Add brown sugar and molasses; taste test, use more or less brown sugar according to taste.
Add lemon juice to desired tartness.
Makes enough for 2 to 3 pounds meat.

title: quicky fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and refrigerate to chill.
Add marshmallows and coconut.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or topping.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder, twice and add.
Add hot milk with butter melted in it.
Add flavoring.
Bake 25 minutes at 365°.

title: casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef; include chopped onion and pepper.
Cook and mash potatoes and add an egg as you mash the potatoes.
Mix hamburger with green beans and tomato soup.
Put this mixture in bottom of casserole dish and put potatoes on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sourdough potato braid
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, combine yeast, 2 cups flour, sugar and salt.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Peel, seed and dice tomatoes.
Finely chop bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients. Shape into a ball and chill.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: CAKE:

Beat well sugar and eggs. Add oil and mix well. Mix in flour and cinnamon. Fold in apples and nuts. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and pierce with a fork.

title: creamless asparagus soup(vegetarian, dairy-free, low-fat)
directions: Melt butter in a large stockpot over medium heat. Add onion, celery and carrots. Cook about 4 minutes until tender. Add salt, thyme, bay leaves, mustard seeds and pepper and stir to coat the vegetables. Add stock, potato and asparagus rounds and bring the mixture to a boil. Reduce heat, partially cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaves; puree half the soup in a blender or food processor and return to pot. Add asparagus tips and simmer 4 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in garlic. Ladle soup into bowls and garnish with dill. Yum! A lot of work, but worth it! Makes 10 cups.

title: pam's cherry crunch
directions: Mix the flour, butter, sugar and nuts.
Spread into an 8 1/2 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: pecan-breaded lamb chops
directions: Beat egg whites slightly in small bowl. Stir in mustard.
Mix pecans, bread crumbs and garlic.
Dip lamb chops into mustard mixture. Coat with pecan mixture.

title: pan coat
directions: Mix together and brush on cooking pans when needed.

title: venison with brown gravy
directions: Roll venison in flour.
Add salt and pepper.
Brown in skillet with hot oil.
Remove and place in crock-pot.
Place soup and water in small saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour over venison.
Let cook all day in crock-pot.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar.
Cut in fat.	Add buttermilk and yeast
mixture.
Knead lightly.
Roll out on lightly floured board 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased pans. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with oleo.
Combine chocolate, Pet milk, sugar, vanilla and instant coffee mixture.

title: valentine (red velvet) cake
directions: Mix ingredients; fill 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, oleo and vanilla.
Beat until creamy; add egg and beat well. Gradually add flour, soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread onto foil lined 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle remaining chocolate chips (2/3 cup) over the top.
Allow to stand until chocolate chips become shiny.
Spread with spatula. Let cool.
Chill 5 to 10 minutes to set chocolate.

title: carrot pineapple bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, undrained pineapple, carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix together.
Add to mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, bottom lined with wax paper; pans greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add seasonings.
Put mixture into pie crust and cover with top crust.
Cut a small hole in center of top crust.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (lowering heat if crust browns too quickly).
Mix stock or bouillon with gelatin and pour slowly through the hole in top crust.
Let cool and chill until the gelatin sets.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus
in
2	quart baking dish.
Break bread into small pieces.
Put over asparagus.	Mix mushroom soup and liquid from
asparagus.
Pour
over bread and asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: curry powder pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; drain.
Combine salt and 8 cups water.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 5 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Put into jars and seal.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: In a 3-quart serving bowl or crystal trifle bowl, layer ingredients in order.
Spread buttermilk Ranch salad dressing over top.
Garnish with bacon bits and croutons.

title: banana bread 1
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in bananas and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch pan or 2 (3 x 7-inch) pans, baking time accordingly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mix.
Stir in chocolate pieces and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: stir-fry beef
directions: In a large skillet sprayed with Pam, add the beef. Cook on low until meat is browned.
Add the tomatoes, bean sprouts and pepper (cut in pieces).
Add the mushrooms, garlic salt and soy sauce. Stir-fry for approximately 45 minutes.
In a pan, cook rice to a boil, then add to stir-fry for 5 minutes. Great meal for 4 people.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Rinse sauerkraut and dry.
On bread, layer 1 slice corned beef, 1/4 cup sauerkraut, 1 slice cheese and 2 teaspoons dressing.
Top with remaining bread. Spread outside with butter and grill in skillet until golden. Serves 4.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients until crumbly.
Combine milk and egg.
Mix until forms a ball.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Pat into arch and cut out biscuits.
Continue until all dough is gone. Bake at 450° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: Microwave ingredients for 5 minutes or until melted.
Drop on wax paper or buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand until hardened, then dip into melted chocolate.
I use the chocolate bark.
At Christmastime, Wal-Mart carries it; Brookshires also carries it.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Bring water, vinegar, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup sugar, onion, bay leaves and peppercorn to a boil.
Pour over meat.
Marinate 24 to 48 hours.
Melt butter in Dutch oven, brown meat 5 minutes on each side.
Add marinade and simmer until tender 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Remove meat and strain liquid.
Add sour cream, heat and serve over sliced meat.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain.
In a shallow casserole, arrange broccoli; top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Or, cover with waxed paper; microwave on High for 6 minutes or until hot, rotating dish half-way through heating.
Serves 4.

title: cherry toast
directions: Dip bread in blended mixture.
Fry in butter. Serve with few spiced cherries.

title: fancy french beans
directions: Cook beans according to package directions.
Add bean sprouts and water chestnuts; heat through.	Drain well and set aside.
In a saucepan melt better.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and cayenne until smooth.
Gradually add cream.
Bring to a boil;
cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add Worcestershire sauce and bean mixture; toss to coat.
Pour into a greased 2-qt. baking dish.
Combine almonds and cheese; sprinkle over the top.
Broil 4-6 inches from the heat for 5 minutes or until almonds are golden brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: hamburger supreme
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Place layer of hamburger on bottom of casserole dish; layer sliced potatoes, potato chips (crushed), cheese, then repeat layers.
Dilute can of cream of mushroom soup as directions indicate.
Pour over dish, poking holes down through so soup runs to bottom.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: citrus oak snack bars(from carnation milk)
directions: In small bowl, cream brown sugar, shortening and zest.
Beat in egg; set aside.
In small bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and mace.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture; beat well after each addition.
Stir in 2/3 cup oats, raisins and wheat germ.
Spread into lightly greased 8-inch square baking pan. Sprinkle top with remaining 2 tablespoons oats.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into 12 bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend soup, mayonnaise, salt and egg together.
Add onion and broccoli and place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cookie cutter cookies
directions: You will also need 4 to 6 cookie cutters of your choice.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine,
shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add
eggs.
Combine
flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed
mixture
alternately with milk
and flavorings.
Fold in pecans.
Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: ground beef snack quiches
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, cook beef, garlic powder and pepper until meat is no longer pink; drain and set aside.

title: mock turkey
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in a pan or pans and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese olives
directions: Mix together margarine, cheese, flour, cayenne pepper, celery seed and green onion until dough is formed.
Press into a ball and roll out into several small squares.
Wrap around olives and chill.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: poppyseed bread
directions: Combine ingredients and mix with mixer.
Use loaf or Bundt cake pan and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, salt, onion and pepper.
Form into balls.
Brown in fat.
Drain.
Cook oil and pineapple juice over low heat for a few minutes.
Add cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add meatballs, pineapple and green pepper.
Heat thoroughly.

title: beef penne pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beef and onion in large saucepan, stirring occasionally, until beef is no longer pink.
Add water, tomato paste, wine and bouillon; cook, stirring occasionally for 10 to 12 minutes or until flavors are blended.
Layer ingredients as follows in ungreased 13 x 9 inch baking dish:
1/2 pasta, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers; cover.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.
Season with salt.

title: impossible ham salad
directions: Layer peas, ham, cheese and onion. Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: bami(pronounced bah-me)
directions: Heat the vegetable oil and sesame oil, then fry the meat.
Add garlic (use garlic press) and onions.
When onions are transparent, add celery and cabbage.
Add pepper.
Stir-fry.
Add snow peas.
Mix in linguine (cooked al dente).
Add soy sauce and stir well over medium heat.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat 1/4 cup oil in large frying pan over high heat.
Add onions and garlic and cook, stirring, until onions are soft but not browned.
Stir in the eggplant, zucchini, peppers, salt, basil and minced parsley.
Add a little oil as needed, only to keep vegetables from sticking.
Cover pan and cook over moderate heat for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, using a large spatula and turning the vegetables to help preserve their shape.
If mixture becomes too soupy, remove cover.
Add tomatoes to vegetables and stir to blend.
Add oil if necessary.
Cover and cook over moderate heat for 15 minutes, stir occasionally.
Garnish with fresh parsley and tomato slices.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil elbows, drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend milk; cook, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Add 1 1/2 cup cheese; stir until melted.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: 1. Combine first 4 ingredients in pan and heat slowly, stir frequently.
When everything is melted, add crme de cacao.

title: caramel ice cream
directions: Caramelize the 12 tablespoons sugar.
Melt in iron skillet. While this is melting, scald 4 cups milk (not boil).
Pour the milk over melted sugar, stirring until melted again.
Separate the eggs, saving whites (to beat later).
Beat egg yolks with sugar (2 cups), flour and can of milk.
Add to first mixture; cook until thick.
Let this cool, then beat egg whites and fold in.
Add vanilla.
Add enough milk to fill freezer.
This makes 1 gallon of ice cream.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: "linda's" barbecue sauerkraut
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in a crock-pot for several hours.

title: spaghetti with garlic
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add oil and heat.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add parsley and toss with hot spaghetti.
Top with grated cheese.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix sugar and corn syrup well and microwave at High for 3 minutes, then add roasted salted peanuts.
Microwave again for 3 or 4 minutes, until light brown. Add butter and vanilla; mix well and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes. Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When done, break into small pieces and store in a tight container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the ingredients and roll in chopped pecans.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Mix together margarine, egg, sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch. Place grated apples in prepared pie crust.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: four layer chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and nuts.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: christmas cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, oil and pudding for 4 minutes, gradually adding the soda. Add nuts and cherries. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a well-greased tube pan.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend (mix) all dry ingredients.
Dip each piece of chicken in margarine and then coat well with dry mixture.
Arrange in shallow open casserole in a single layer. Pour remaining margarine over all.
Place in preheated oven uncovered and bake for 1 hour.
Do not turn!

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes on top of stove until almost tender.
Mix rest of ingredients and cook until thick.
In 2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook ground beef and drain fat.
Mix all ingredients together. Roll in egg skins and deep fry.

title: wanda's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Add 1 Tbsp. sugar and beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients together, mix in butter, add liquid mixture - knead a little.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Roll into large circle.
Brush with melted butter.
Cut into wedge-shaped pieces.
Roll each piece starting with wide end.
Let rise 4-5 hours.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients including the shrimp juice.
Chill for about 1 hour before serving.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Put ham bone in a large kettle with cold water and simmer 1 1/2 hours, keeping the lid tightly closed.
Do not boil.
Add peas, carrots, onion, celery and seasonings and continue to simmer one more hour or until peas are very soft. Remove ham bone.
Rub soup through sieve and return to kettle. Season further to suit taste, adding salt only if necessary.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll tightly and wrap separately in plastic wraps.
Chill.
Cut in 1-inch slices before serving.
You can freeze for later if need be.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar and oil.
Blend well. Add rest of ingredients, one at a time, in order given. Mix well after each addition.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15. Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: divinity
directions: In saucepan, mix first 4 ingredients.
Slowly bring to a boil. Boil to hard ball stage.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and butter. Add eggs one at the time. Beat well after each egg. Add flour, salt & baking powder, then milk & vanilla. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour & 25 minutes.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic. Add prepared beans, water, enchilada sauce, stewed tomatoes and olives to pan; simmer until cooked. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Stir in 1/2 pint sour cream and some tortilla strips. Serve with a few tortilla strips on top, a dollop of sour cream and a sprinkle of grated cheese.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cube cooked chicken and mix with other ingredients and cover with buttered corn flakes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Add corn muffin mix, yogurt and corn.
Mix well.
Put in 2 1/2-quart dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl and mix for 5 minutes. Pour into a 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 70 minutes.
Cool and frost with butter icing.

title: new year's day soup
directions: Saute ham, celery, onion, carrots and garlic in Dutch oven until tender. Stir in black-eyed peas, chicken broth, stewed tomatoes, diced tomatoes and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes. Stir in spinach, parsley and pepper.

title: delicious pork loin
directions: Wash pork loin.
With long, sharp, pointed knife, cut an opening through the center lengthwise.
Stuff with prunes.
Season to taste.

title: sweet potato pudding cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Cream butter, sugars and pudding mix.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Alternately add dry ingredients and potatoes to mixture.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
You can also add 1 cup nuts or chocolate chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; add salt, 1 tablespoon margarine and rice.
Cover pan; reduce heat to medium. Cook for 20 minutes.
In the meantime, cook the fresh or frozen broccoli.
Drain the water chestnuts and crush the Ritz crackers. When rice is done, add to broccoli along with water chestnuts and Cheez Whiz.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with the Ritz crackers mixed with melted 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly about 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Cook onion until tender in melted Crisco.
Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese. Cover and cook over moderately low heat about 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves, stir in cheese and heat until melted.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well, then layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish with vanilla wafers.
Start with wafers and alternate.
Try to make 3 layers.
Mix the last 5 ingredients in a saucepan; cook for 1 minute.
Let cool; pour over the other mixture.
Top with chopped pecans.

title: chinese new year rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecued sage spareribs
directions: Place ribs in a Dutch oven and cover with water. Add onion, garlic, pickling spices, sage and hot pepper sauce. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 90 minutes or until tender. Cool slightly. Rinse ribs with water to remove spices. Pour barbecue sauce into a large resealable plastic bag or shallow baking dish. Add ribs; cover and refrigerate overnight. Bring to room temperature. Drain, reserving marinade. Grill ribs, uncovered, over medium heat, turning several times until browned and heated through, about 10 minutes. Place marinade in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Brush over the ribs.

title: german chocolate caramel supreme
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While the cake is hot, punch holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping over it to soak in.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath crumbs on top before serving.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: lillian's sweet potatoes and pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and boil whole sweet potatoes until done; drain and dip in drained pineapple juice.
Roll in crushed corn flakes and place in baking pan.
Cover potatoes with crushed pineapple and top with maraschino cherries.
Bake approximately 10 to 12 minutes until potatoes and pineapple are thoroughly heated.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water together until it will form a hard ball when dropped in water. Beat egg whites and salt at high speed for 3 minutes in a large bowl.
Pour syrup slowly into beaten whites while beating at high speed. Continue beating until passed the glossy stage. Add nuts or fruits and vanilla.
Continue beating until mixture forms a peak.
Pour into buttered platter or drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender in a small amount of boiling water; drain.
Combine carrots, onion and green pepper; set aside. Combine catsup, salad oil, vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Refrigerate overnight.
Carrots will keep for several days in the refrigerator.

title: rosie's jello pie
directions: Boil 7-Up; add jello and stir until jello is dissolved.
Add ice cream; stir until ice cream is melted.
Let cool (not set). Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: aggression cookies
directions: There is only one way to mix this and that is to use your hands.
Knead until there aren't any lumps of margarine.
Roll the dough into small balls and place them on an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten gently with a small fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Cool before removing from cookie sheet.
This recipe makes 10 to 15 dozen cookies.
Good to do when you are angry or upset.
Works off your "aggressions."

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Make pudding according to package directions but using only 1 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on half the graham crackers.
Top with remaining graham crackers. Place the sandwiches in a container and cover with plastic wrap. Freeze until firm (about 5 to 6 hours).
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: swiss steak deluxe
directions: Add salt and pepper to the flour and pound into meat.
In large skillet, add the olive oil and brown the meat.
Add the onion, green pepper, boiling water and ketchup.
Cover closely; simmer slowly until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy raisin delight(sandwiches)
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all together except bread into cream cheese.
Spread mixture on raisin bread.
This is perfect for school lunches!!

title: tuna plate pyramids
directions: Combine tuna, cream cheese, onion, salt and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Mound onto crackers; shape into pyramids with edge of knife or spatula.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, syrup, canned cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add salt and chopped nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Add clams with lemon juice.
Add all spices; saute one minute.
Add breadcrumbs.
Remove from heat. Put into casserole dish.
Cover with strips of Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake until bubbly.

title: crumb top apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt and alternate layers with apples in bottom of pie crust.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Spray a 2-quart square casserole dish with Pam.
Pour in mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 9 squares at 166 calories each.
Using Butter Buds saves 40 calories per serving.

title: never fail yeast rolls
directions: In small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk.
In large bowl, put sugar, fat and salt.
Pour scalded milk over this mixture.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add egg and yeast mixture.
Combine flour with mixture.
Knead until shiny and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover; let rise.
Punch down; let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in hot water.
Add lemon juice and onion juice.
Stir.
Let cool and start to congeal.
Add sour cream and grated cucumber.
Mix. Place in refrigerator and let congeal.

title: best cookie ever
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and sugars in a large bowl.
Mix in the eggs and vanilla extract, then the flour, oatmeal, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix.

title: beans supreme
directions: Cook beans until nearly done and add remaining ingredients. Cook all together 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pilaf
directions: In a large skillet put the oleo, mushrooms and onions.
Saute until oil is melted good over the onions and mushrooms.
In an oblong cake pan, put the rice, consomme and cumin.
Pour oleo mixture in with rice mixture. Stir real good.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir one time while baking.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix together oleo
and	cookies
and press into 8 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and cool.

title: mom's snow cream
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add snow to make as thick as you want.
Enjoy.

title: fruited ice tea
directions: Boil water and instant tea.
Stir well.
Add sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Serve over ice.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars and margarine until creamy.
Whip eggs in, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir in flour mixture into first mixture and then add oats, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 7 or 8 dozen.

title: quick and easy party punch
directions: Chill all liquid ingredients.
Pour into large punch bowl. Float sherbet on top.
Stir while serving.

title: alison swope's jalapeno corn muffins(makes 48 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the cornmeal, flour, salt and baking powder thoroughly in a bowl.
Combine the onion, pepper, butter, corn, sour cream, eggs and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour muffin tins; fill the muffin cups halfway with the batter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden and a toothpick inserted into the muffins comes out clean.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Cook barley in 1 1/2 cups stock or water until tender.
Add remaining stock, tamari and sherry.
Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add mushrooms and salt.
When cooked tender, add to barley mixture, including liquid from cooking.
Add generous grinding of pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered, on the lowest possible heat.
Taste to correct seasoning.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar, orange peel and vanilla.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy; stir in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend in creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half and chill 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll to 1/8-inch.
Cut in desired shapes with cutters.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Cool on rack and decorate.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mint cookies
directions: Melt chocolate; add oil.
Dip crackers in chocolate to coat both sides and place on wax paper to cool and harden.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 4 tablespoons water.
Add 1 cup boiling water, lemon juice, juice from pineapple and sugar.
Let set in freezing compartment about 15 minutes or until syrupy.

title: icebox pickles
directions: You will need a 1-gallon jar.

title: french-style fudge
directions: In large glass bowl, thoroughly combine milk and sugar. Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla, walnuts and chips to hot mixture.
Stir until completely blended.
Pour into buttered 3-quart dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: chicken, gravy and dressing casserole
directions: Bone chicken; leave in large pieces and arrange in bottom of baking dish.
Spoon soup from can over chicken.
Mix dressing with broth from cooked chicken.
Spread dressing evenly over soup and chicken.
Bake at 400° until dressing is done.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Add 1/2 package cut-up cream cheese the last 5 to 10 minutes of baking time.

title: rice parisian
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add mushrooms and rice, saute until brown.
Add soup mix and water.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: patsy's punch
directions: Mix the ingredients and complete the gallon with water.
Mix and serve.
May be frozen ahead and thawed before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, cornmeal and salt.
Mix in milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake until set.
Serve it plain or with a meringue made with the four egg whites.

title: barbecued marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in mixture of first 6 ingredients (easiest in a Ziploc bag; turn occasionally). Microwave chicken 18 minutes on High. Immediately transfer to barbecue and cook about 10 minutes longer, basting with marinade. (Discard excess marinade.)

title: potato soup
directions: Bring to a boil onion, carrot, celery and parsley in 4 cups water.
(It is important to measure water.)
Season with salt and pepper.
Lower heat and cook for 15 minutes (covered).
Add potatoes, mushrooms and marjoram.
Cook until potatoes are done, about 30 minutes.
Combine flour and margarine.
Stir into soup. Cook 5 minutes, stirring as mixture thickens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until thickened.
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: party maple pecan pie
directions: Cook Eagle Brand milk, syrup and salt in heavy saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add nuts.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped cream and toasted coconut.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger,
onion
and
green pepper; drain.
Add beans, soup, milk, taco sauce and taco seasoning.	Put 1/2 bag of Doritos in	bottom	of
9-inch
pan.
Pour
1/2 meat mixture over chips.
Sprinkle
with
some grated cheese.
Add more chips, meat mixture and top with more cheese.
Bake until cheese melts in 350° oven, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter frosting *
directions: Blend butters.
Add sugar alternately with cream.
Blend until smooth.
Makes enough to frost 36 cupcakes or tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: sesame oven-fried fish
directions: Pour milk into shallow dish. Combine bread crumbs, cornmeal, sesame seed, seasoning, dry mustard, garlic powder and pepper in bowl. Dip fish into milk. Coat with crumb mixture. Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Place fish in baking pan. Sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 450° for 4 to 6 minutes per 2-inches of thickness until fish is golden and flakes easily.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter over medium heat in skillet.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Add to skillet with 3/4 cup brown sugar. Sprinkle with a little cinnamon.
Fry until tender.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Skin and place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with seasoning, lemon juice and soy sauce.
Cover and cook full power until chicken is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together coconut cream pudding, French vanilla pudding and milk. Add Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add coconut, however much you want.
Pour over graham cracker crust. Put Cool Whip on top and toasted coconut.

title: winter soup(studebaker style)
directions: Combine tomato
juice, water, bouillon cubes, vegetable flakes, onion flakes, parsley
and Tabasco in stock pot; bring to a boil and
cut
to
simmer.
Add
remaining
ingredients. Simmer about 1 1/2 to
2 hours.
Freezes very well.
May add 2 pounds ground beef, browned,
drained and patted dry to remove excess fat.
Serve
with
grilled
cheese sandwiches and fruit dessert.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt; blend well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Combine 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Roll ball into sugar mixture. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: hamburger-beans soup
directions: Wash beans.
Add water and boil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, celery, carrots, onion, rice, bouillon cubes and hamburger.
Season to taste.
Add bay leaf.
Yields 10 servings.

title: lime cream cheese salad
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over first 3 ingredients.
When marshmallows and cream cheese are nearly dissolved, add 1 cup cold water.
Let set until partially jelled.
Then add last 2 ingredients.
Beat together.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: melt in your mouth venison tenderloin fillets
directions: Cut slightly frozen fillets in 1/4-inch slices. Lightly pound fillets.
Dust with seasoned flour.

Melt equal parts of butter and oil in fry pan, enough to generously cover the bottom of pan. When oil is hot, add fillets and cook about 1 minute on each side. Repeat cooking steps until all the meat is cooked.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine
sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan.
Stir until sugar and cornstarch are dissolved.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly,
until	thick
and clear.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.	Cool to room temperature.

title: fried chicken
directions: Put vinegar and onion slices in dish or bowl.
Place chicken parts in mixture and marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Turn at least once while marinating.

title: chinese pepper steak with rice
directions: Melt Crisco or drippings.
Add beef and brown slowly over a low flame.
Add onion, green peppers, celery and 1/2 cup liquid. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Thicken with cornstarch blended with water and soy sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot with boiled rice.
Serves 4.

title: frosty fruit cubes
directions: Prepare instant pudding mix according to package directions. Stir in dessert topping, mayonnaise or salad dressing and lemon juice.
Combine pineapple, bananas and almonds.
Fold into pudding mixture.
Turn mixture into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add milk.
Mix all other ingredients in a blender or by hand.
Then stir into milk and cheese mixture.
Cook 20 minutes.
When cool, add mayonnaise. Makes 2 pints.

title: sweet 'n spicy dunk
directions: Cut franks on a slant into 3/4-inch chunks.
Combine franks and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until smooth.
Serve warm.
Use toothpicks to spear franks.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Combine butter, sugar and about half the flour until mixed. Add the rest of flour and vanilla.
Work with hands until smooth. Chill.
Flatten dough to cover a 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Press edges with fork.
Prick with fork here and there.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 45 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: shower punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (about 15 minutes before serving time). Delicious!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Roll in chives and paprika for red and green Christmas effect or roll in chopped nuts.

title: sherry beef casserole dish
directions: Add jar of mushroom and parsley, if so desired, makes it much better.
Put all ingredients together and stir in a casserole or crock-pot.
Cover and cook at 325° for 3 hours.
Be sure container is large enough so it doesn't run over.
Great over large egg noodles or mashed potatoes as a main dish.

title: mushroom and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, butter and mushrooms.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and rice together in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add sauteed mixture and stir.
Add beef broth, slowly stirring the mixture. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Stir after 30 minutes.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; mix in egg and butter with fork. Spread 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13 pan.
Pour can of cherries on top and spread remaining mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine ingredients (do not drain salmon) except additional crumbs and butter, mixing with a fork until blended.
Shape into 9 patties, using 1/4 cup each.
Flatten out slightly.
Dip into the additional crumbs.
Preheat electric frypan to 320°.
When light goes out, melt butter.
Add patties, brown, turning to brown on both sides.
Can be served with chili sauce or catsup; we eat them plain.
Garnish with parsley.

title: crock-pot snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot until mixed and coated; cook low 3 - 4 hours; uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in double boiler.
Stir once.
Cook over low heat until liquid is in half (about 15 minutes).
Strain and let cool.
Should have 1/4 cup.
Beat yolks until frothy.
Beat vinegar mixture into yolks.
Put over hot water (not touching pan) over low heat.
Add butter, 1 pat at a time, beating constantly until smooth.
Cool, then chill.
Don't cover.
Serve at room temperature.

title: "chicken lickin" good pork chops
directions: Flour pork chops with seasoned flour.
Sprinkle each with garlic, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Brown on both sides in a small amount of hot oil.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add remaining ingredients.
Form small balls and push down flat with bottom of glass, dipped in water.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: valentine fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well before serving (overnight works well).

title: grandmother's lane cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift.
Cream butter gradually, adding sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Stir in vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes, or until done.
Let cool on cake racks.
Put together with the filling.
Cover all with boiled or 7 minute icing.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain well.
Measure noodles and cook in boiling water. Drain noodles.

title: cake for birds in winter
directions: Mix all together; put into a pan and let it dry until hard.
Do not bake.
Use in bird feeder in winter.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in large mixer bowl.
Blend well; then beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 13 X 9 pan (spray with Pam).
Bake 350 degrees for 1 hour or until cake is done.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Prick holes in cake with a fork.
Thoroughly blend lemonade and powdered sugar. Gradually spoon over cake until completely absorbed.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: valarie's party pink divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in buttered heavy 2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Cook, without stirring, to hard ball stage, 250°. Remove from heat. Beat egg whites in a large bowl of mixer until soft peaks form. Gradually add gelatin, beating until stiff peaks form. Slowly pour in syrup, beating constantly at high speed. Continue beating until mixture begins to lose its gloss. Stir in chopped nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper or into small paper muffin liners. Sprinkle with tinted coconut.
Makes about 2 pounds or 4 dozen medium size pieces of candy.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender and lightly browned. Combine all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cracker crumbs for top.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with reserved 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: rhubarb juice
directions: Fill 4-quart kettle half full with cut up rhubarb, then fill with water.
Bring to a boil.
Let stand 1/2 hour, then drain. (This can be canned.)
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Saute onions; add to softened cream cheese
and
ounce
sour cream.	Add pepper.
Mix all together. Put
tablespoons mixture on flour tortilla; roll up.
Place in baking
dish.
Mix
ounces
sour cream and 4 ounces
chicken broth together.
Pour over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and a few chili peppers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips and salsa.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pack firmly into a 9 x 5-inch pan.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan. Add to grease the brown sugar, vinegar and onions.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix water, vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard and pepper.
Add lemon and onion.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce and smoke.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over chops and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: glazed almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flavorings and egg yolks, then flour, salt and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in unbeaten egg whites and put 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put whole almond on top of each and flatten some.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.
Good keeper.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine instant pudding and milk.
Add ice cream and beat on low speed until well blended.
Pour over cake cubes. Set aside until firm. Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add frozen strawberries. Stir until begins to thicken.
Pour over pudding. Do not stir.
Use a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole for serving from. Chill until set.

title: easy sausage pizza bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Cook and stir sausage and onion in 10-inch skillet until sausage is brown; drain.
Mix baking mix and beer until thoroughly moistened; spread batter in pan.
Spread spaghetti sauce carefully over batter.
Top with sausage mixture and the remaining ingredients.
Bake until crust is golden brown, 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Stir and let set for 20 minutes.
Put in freezer bags.
Very good.

title: aunt hermia's raw apple cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together in a bowl.
Add the second group of ingredients and mix.
Pour the mixture into a greased or sprayed 8 x 8 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook celery, onion, scallions and cabbage in oil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in salt, pepper and meat.
Drain off excess water, cool.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling on one corner of egg roll wrapper and roll up, tucking opposite end in.
Seal with a little water.
Fry in deep hot oil until brown.
Serve with hot mustard and duck sauce.
Makes 8 to 10 egg rolls.

title: cool whip jello recipe
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Top with fresh fruit and pecan chips.
Don't forget to drain pineapple.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 10-inch cake pan.
Mix soup with melted margarine.
Add pretzels.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: easy oven roast
directions: Note:
Need 1 large oven cooking bag.

title: lemon shaker pie
directions: Peel and slice the lemons, removing the seeds.
Place the sliced lemons in a large bowl.
Add the sugar; mix together until sugar is dissolved.
Let set, covered, overnight.

title: green beans caesar
directions: In bowl, toss green beans, vinegar and oil. Spread in low baking dish. Set aside. In small saucepan, melt margarine and Parmesan cheese. Mix in crackers ( that have already been crumbled) to make crumbly mixture. Sprinkle on beans and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Delicious served with baked ham or to accompany any dish!

title: ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Peel, cut up and remove seeds from cukes.
Boil all ingredients in 1-quart of vinegar until cukes are tender.
Makes 8 pints of very sweet pickles.

title: creme brulee
directions: Put the cream into a heatproof bowl over a pan of hot water and heat gently (do not boil).
Beat the egg yolks with 2 ounces sugar.
Stir in the cream.
Divide the custard equally between 6 ramekins.
Stand dishes in a roasting pan containing enough hot water to come halfway up the sides of the dishes.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour or until set.
Remove from the pan and allow to cool, then chill overnight.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Clean, slice and cool carrots, just until they begin to soften (15 to 20 minutes). Drain. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over hot carrots. Cover and chill in refrigerator for at least 6 hours.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In an oblong casserole dish, mix all ingredients; top with pineapple rings and bacon strips, if desired.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken dinner
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from broth and reserve.
Remove chicken from bone, cut into small pieces.
In 9 x 13 pan, combine chicken soup, chicken pieces, broth, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place in preheated 400° oven.
Bake until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from oven, place biscuits on top of mixture.
Return to oven baking until golden brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Work with a spoon.
Cover and refrigerate until needed.
Spoon out on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Beat yolks thick and light.
Blend in beer, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Beat whites stiff, but not dry. Fold into beer mixture.
Pat fish dry.
Dip and fry in deep fat (375°) for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden and puffed.

title: toll house quick ice cream
directions: In heavy-gauge saucepan, combine brown sugar and butter. Bring to boil over low heat, stirring occasionally; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.

title: maraschino cherry cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and egg yolks in a pan.
Mix water, milk and cherry juice.
Mix with first 4 ingredients.
Beat together.
Cook in heavy saucepan until thickened.
Add chopped cherries, oleo and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake until meringue is lightly browned.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat
eggs, add sugar and mix together.
Melt margarine and add
to egg and sugar mixture.
Blend in vanilla and stir well; add milk slowly (stirring with mixer while adding).
Add coconut and mix well; pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 60 minutes at 350° until nice and brown.
Makes 2 deep dish pies.

title: no sugar popsicles
directions: Pour juice into containers and freeze.

title: martha's cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except parsley flakes.
Form into a ball.
Sprinkle parsley flakes on.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrots and onion in water until tender; drain. Add sour cream and chicken soup; mix.
Melt butter; mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 in baking dish; add squash mixture, then put the rest of stuffing on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 1/2 hour in microwave.

title: delicious broccoli and chicken salad(serves 4)
directions: Cut the broccoli into small flowerets.
Blanch in boiling water with peanut oil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and plunge into cold water.
Drain and chill.
Cook the chicken breasts by either roasting or poaching.
Debone, cut up and chill.
Assemble the salad.
Add parsley and onions and toss with Cottage Cheese and Dill Dressing.

title: lima bean salad(salata fasoolya)
directions: Boil beans until tender and drain.
Add salt, garlic, lemon juice and oil to beans.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve hot or cold.

title: salzburger nockerln mit himbeersauce(sweet souffle of beaten egg whites with raspberry sauce)
directions: Start with heating up the oven.
Whip the egg whites until they are stiff.
Add the sugar fluently.
Take care that the egg whites are really very stiff, because that's very important for your success.
Add the yolks slowly and fold in the flour carefully. Melt the butter and fill it in a fireproof bowl.
Form 3 dumplings and lay them in the buttered bowl.
Bake the "Nockerl" for about 5 to 7 minutes.
Vanilla sugar the souffle.
Strain the raspberries in the mixer and sugar the sauce to taste.
Serve quickly on a ground of raspberry sauce.
Serve with Frittatensuppe, Zwiebelrostbraten mit Bratkartoffel.

title: rigatoni al forno(noodles with mushrooms, sausage and mozzarella)
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy large casserole and add the onion.
Cook, stirring, until wilted.
If the mushrooms are tiny, leave them whole.
Otherwise, quarter them or slice them, depending on size.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook cheese in soups until cheese melts.
Place ground beef in casserole dish.
Add cheese mixture (pour over).
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until Tater Tots are brown.

title: chicken and cheese
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish, skin side down.
Add sour cream, cheese, mushrooms and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chili chicken casserole(serves 6)
directions: Line bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with chips.
Saute chicken, onion and garlic in oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheeses.
Pour over chips. Sprinkle grated cheeses on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cover and cook onion and celery in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, pepper and mustard.
Add milk and broth.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in cheese; heat over low heat, stirring occasionally, just until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Makes 4 servings; contains 355 calories per serving.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix flour and spices and add to creamed mixture.
Combine soda and applesauce and add last.
Stir in pecans, if desired.
Store batter, covered, in refrigerator (up to 2 weeks).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add water to vegetables; boil 5 minutes.
Pour hot into hot canning jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to each pint, or 1/2 teaspoon salt to each quart.
Adjust caps. Process pints 55 minutes, quarts 1 hour and 25 minutes at 10 pounds pressure in pressure canner.
Yields about 7 quarts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 400°.
Top with potato chips or onion rings.

title: c. b. salad
directions: Chop cauliflower and broccoli in small pieces; set aside.

title: toast sticks
directions: Cut off edges of bread.
Toast end pieces and edge of bread in oven.
Roll into crumbs.
Cut bread into 6 sticks per slice.
Put on cookie sheet and put in 200° oven until good and dry.
Melt peanut butter, sugar and oil over low heat.
Dip bread sticks in mixture, then roll in crumbs.
Let dry at least 1 hour before storing in an airtight container.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Reserve 3 tablespoons mixture for topping, if desired.
Press remaining mixture firmly against bottom and side of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake as directed for 10 minutes.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Saute onions in shortening; add beef and brown.
Add other ingredients and cover.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish and cover with 1 cup corn bread batter or 1 envelope of corn bread mix.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water until tender.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown pork in a skillet in a small amount of soy sauce or saute shrimp in soy sauce; add chopped green onions and saute until slightly soft.
Then add the scrambled eggs.
Stir into mixture; then add rice mix.
Add ketchup and soy sauce to taste. Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange-chocolate bombe
directions: You will also need popsicle sticks and 10 (3 ounce size) waxed paper drink cups.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash sweet potatoes.
Grease with butter.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until fork tender.
Peel while hot and slice.
Place in casserole dish.

title: hard sauce
directions: Cream oleo with powdered sugar.
Add boiling water slowly to beaten egg yolks and continue beating until light and lemon colored.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in egg whites, beat stiff but not dry.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts or 50 servings.
Wonderful over Bread Pudding.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and vanilla pudding; whip.
Add powdered sugar and Cool Whip and blend well.
Place whole graham crackers at bottom of pan, then add a layer of pudding, a layer of graham crackers and rest of pudding.
Put final layer of graham crackers and then put chocolate frosting on top of last layer of graham crackers. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dissolved gelatin and lemon juice.
Add shrimp, celery, eggs, salt, pepper, onion and hot sauce.
Put in lightly oiled fish mold and chill.
Unmold and serve with crackers and Melba toast.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Bake hen until tender; remove meat from pan, reserving liquid. Combine cubed chicken with undiluted soups; set aside.
Make dressing with all ingredients, except eggs; moisten with chicken broth.
Spread a layer of dressing in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread chicken mixture over layer of dressing.
Mix remaining dressing with 2 eggs and top the chicken layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until brown.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While warm, poke holes into cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Put on in layers:
first, all of the milk, then butterscotch and last the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with candy. Chill, covered, in refrigerator.
This is "sinfully delicious".

title: double corn muffins
directions: Mix all above well.
Use 8 x 11-inch greased pan or 12 muffin pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 50 minutes.

title: scalloped fish
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over very low heat.
Add salt, pepper and onion; cook for 1 minute or so, until tender.
Stir in the flour, then stir the milk in slowly, cooking until smooth and slightly thickened.
Add the Worcestershire sauce and cook again until thick.
Check the seasoning.
Grease a 1-quart casserole or individual baking dishes.
Arrange alternate layers of fish and sauce.
Top with the cheese mixed with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, or until bubbly and browned.
Serves 4.

title: chicken chili
directions: Mix together and put in crock-pot; cook all day on low.

title: garlic grits
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; add grits and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add butter and garlic cheese; stir until melted.
Put eggs in measuring cup and add milk to make 1 cup; beat and add to grits.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Pour cereal over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cool completely.
Coat macaroni with mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients and a dash of salt.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: chicken-liver loaf
directions: In skillet, saute onions and garlic in butter until lightly browned.
Add livers and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until juices no longer flow.
In food processor, puree liver mixture until smooth. In a large bowl, beat remaining ingredients.
Stir in liver puree (mixture will be thin).
Turn into greased 7 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Cool, then chill thoroughly in pan.
To serve, run knife around edge and unmold. Slice 1/2 inch thick.
Makes 14 slices (108 calories per slice).

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Finely dice salt pork.
Brown over low heat and remove crisp bits.
Make tiny meatballs from mixture above (1 to 1 1/2-inch diameter).
Brown in salt pork fat.
When brown on all sides, remove to bowl.
Rub flour into drippings and cook.
Add water and salt for gravy.
Return meatballs and pour bits to gravy and simmer, covered, 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheez-Its and butter.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle Cheez-Its on top.
Drizzle melted butter on top of Cheez-Its.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt butter in large skillet over low heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is limp but not brown.
Remove from heat and add chicken, chilies and cream cheese.
Mix lightly with a fork, adding salt to taste.
Spoon about 1/3 cup filling down center of each tortilla.
Set seam side down in baking dish; moisten tops with cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered until heated through.
Garnish with green onions and olives.

title: uncle roy's baked corn
directions: Mix corn, eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add milk; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Dot with butter and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel pie
directions: Sprinkle 3/4 cup of sugar evenly in a 10-inch cast-iron skillet; place over medium heat.
Caramelize sugar by constantly stirring with a wooden spoon.
Remove sugar from heat.
Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly.
Combine 3/4 cup of sugar and flour.
Add to caramelized sugar mixture.
Beat egg yolks. Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into yolks; add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Return to low heat. Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add butter, vanilla and pinch of salt, stirring well.
Spoon custard into shell.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add half of mixture to butter and vanilla.
Add half of the milk.
Mix well.
Add remaining sugar mixture and milk.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; add chocolate.
Stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Allow to cool before cutting.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Stir together cake mix, eggs and margarine.
Batter will be stiff.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: oven-baked round steak with mushroom sauce
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut round steak into serving-size pieces. Heat a skillet with 2 tablespoons oil until hot.
Put flour on a plate.
One at a time, flour round steaks and put immediately into hot skillet without crowding.
Brown quickly on one side, then quickly on the other, adding 1 tablespoon of oil as needed.
Put browned steaks into roaster or heatproof heavy casserole.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, nutmeg, paprika and salt until smooth.
Stir in sherry, then seafood; cook until heated through. Combine cream and egg yolks and slowly pour into mixture; stir constantly, continuing until thick and smooth.
Serve with toast points.
Top with bread crumbs and bake until brown, if desired.

title: caribbean ratatouille
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Saute onions and garlic until soft (about 5 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low, cover saucepan and simmer, stirring occasionally until vegetables are tender (about 30 minutes).
Add additional seasonings to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: island rice
directions: In skillet melt 2
tablespoons	butter.
Add rice; cook until light brown.
Turn into
1 1/2 quart casserole.
Pour in water and stir with fork.
Cover
with
foil	and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Blend, chill and serve.
Great on rye or wheat crackers.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Beat in sugar until smooth.
Add flour, salt and vanilla; mixture will be stiff.
Pinch off small pieces of dough with moistened fingers; roll into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in 375° oven for 13 to 14 minutes, until bottoms are golden.
Do not let tops brown.
When done, roll in powdered sugar.

title: english trifle
directions: Make jello and let set until cool.
Lay ladyfingers in jello. Add fruit cocktail and strawberries.
Let set in refrigerator and then make pudding.
When cold, put on top of jello.
Let set again.
Put Cool Whip on top and decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Use 13 x 9-inch pan. Immediately after removing from oven, punch holes in cake with fork evenly everywhere.
Take 1 can pina colada mix and pour on top of cake with condensed milk on top.
Don't stir or try to mix. Cool cake completely.
Take half the container of Cool Whip. Take can of pie filling and spread evenly on top of this layer. Put remaining Cool Whip on top of pie filling.
Sprinkle with nuts; chill overnight.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake, pudding
and
oil;
beat
eggs
in,
one at a time. Add 7-Up.
