Pour into three prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool, then fill between layers, top and sides with desired topping.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Split muffins; place on cookie sheets.
Put pizza sauce on muffins, then cheese, then pepperoni.
Can add any topping you like, onions, hamburg, green peppers, whatever you prefer.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is all melted.

title: granola
directions: Mix oats, nuts and salt.
Blend remaining ingredients together well and mix into oats.
Bake at 225°.
Turn every 1/2 hour until golden.
Add raisins when cool.

title: spanish hominy
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in bacon drippings in a large skillet until tender. Add tomatoes; cook over medium heat 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; cook an additional 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually add the beaten egg and milk until well blended.
Let mixture stand 15 minutes.
Heat 1/3 inch of oil in a deep skillet or deep fryer to 390°.
When oil is hot, pour the batter into a funnel, drizzling in a thin stream of batter into hot oil.
Start in the center of the skillet, circling continuously until pan is filled or cake is to desired size.
Do not stop pouring until cake is complete.
Fry on each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm with powdered sugar for dipping.
Makes 6 large funnel cakes.

title: wassail
directions: Mix in crock-pot on high until mixture begins to become hot. Turn to low.
Season to taste.
It becomes sweeter as it warms. Stir before serving. Great for cool weather!

title: hawaiian sunset cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Beat 3 minutes on medium speed. Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool layers.

title: pumpkin cider bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs.
Add pumpkin, cider and milk mixed with vinegar.
Blend well.
Combine dry ingredients in order given and stir into first mixture.
Add nuts and raisins. Pour into two 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Scald milk, then add sugar, butter and salt, stirring until dissolved.
When lukewarm, add yeast, dissolved in lukewarm water plus sugar.
Beat in egg, then add flour, stirring in part of the flour.
Knead in the rest.
Use only enough flour to form a dough that can be handled easily.
Place dough into a bowl; brush top with melted butter (oleo).
Cover bowl; let dough rise in a warm place until it doubles in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: christmas date cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Place pan of water in bottom of oven. Chop
dates
and pecans; add cherries (candied cherries or maraschino is preferred).
Add vanilla and liquid (wine or grape juice can be substituted for whiskey) to fruit and nuts. Stir
in sugar
and
slightly
beaten egg yolks.
Stir in dry ingredients and fold in beaten egg whites.
Batter will appear stiff and be mostly
fruit
and nuts.
Decorate top with nuts and cherries. Bake cake at least 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef in shortening; drain.
Add onion to boiling water and simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushroom soup, salt and pepper to the cooked onion.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with a layer of potatoes, then a layer of ground beef.
Top with onion soup mixture.
Continue alternating layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between outside and center of filling comes out clean. Cool before serving.
(Double recipe makes 3 pies.)

title: sugar-free fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate and Equal, stirring to remove all lumps. Place over low heat and stir in chocolate. Cook until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and add Equal. Makes 16 servings. Contains 20 calories.
Exchange: Free.

title: bunelos(fried sugar tortillas)
directions: In saucepan, heat milk and butter to boiling; cool.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; add egg mixture and mix well.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.
Shape into 20 balls.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Roll each ball into a 4-inch circle.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breasts between wax paper.
Pound to flatten to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place cheese and ham on chicken.
Roll up the chicken breast and fasten edges with toothpicks.
Mix flour and paprika on wax paper and coat chicken.
Place chicken in a 2-quart dish.
Melt butter on High for 45 seconds or until melted. Drizzle butter over chicken.
Cook 5 minutes on High.
Add wine and bouillon.
Microwave on 70% power for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Blend cornstarch and cream; gradually add to chicken.
Cook on 70% power for 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Drain 1 can pork and beans, 1 can kidney beans, 1 can butter beans, drained. 1 can green beans, drained.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat
1 cup milk and butter in double boiler.
Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Add 1/2 cup milk and egg yolks; mix well.
Pour this mixture into hot milk and butter.
Cook until thick, stirring all the time.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: egg in a nest
directions: Cut a circle in the center of the slice of bread.
Put 2 tablespoons butter in frying pan on medium heat and when hot, fry bread slice on one side.
Turn bread over and turn head down. Break an egg in the middle of the hole.
Sprinkle salt and butter. Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Toast and cube bread.
Place bread cubes in buttered baking dish.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Scald the chocolate milk and pour over bread cubes. Add butter to bread and milk so it will melt.
Add other combined ingredients.
Mix together with spoon.
Bake at 375° until golden brown or knife comes out clean, approximately 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream topping.

title: fat-free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients and raisins.
Add egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla; stir until well blended.
(Dough will be stiff). Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes or just until firm.
Do not overbake. Remove; cool on wire rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.
(No grams fat).

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order as they are listed.
Store overnight in refrigerator.
Do not mix or toss before serving.

title: chocolate raspberry streusel square
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup oat mixture for streusel.
Press remaining oat mixture onto bottom of ungreased 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spread preserves over crust.
Sprinkle evenly with chocolate chips. Combine reserved oat mixture and almonds.
Sprinkle over chocolate chips.
Pat gently.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until brown.
Cool and drizzle with melted chocolate.
Let set before cutting.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: clam dip
directions: Cream the cheese until smooth.
Add all ingredients.
Chill. Serve on crackers or party loaf bread.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar and mustard. Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of tomato sauce mixture and stir thoroughly.
Place meat mixture in microproof round casserole.
Pour remaining sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 12 to 14 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add flour and cheese. Drain apples.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend whipped topping and sour cream by hand.
Continue blending and add remaining ingredients.
Use for all fruits.

title: chocolate frozen treats
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze on sticks or in freezer pop containers.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: mustard dill sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine. Stir in flour and gradually add 1 cup of the milk. Simmer for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir in mustard, dill and the remaining 1/4 cup of milk. Serve with fish or salmon loaf.

title: creamy chicken 'n noodles
directions: Heat Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in large deep skillet on medium heat.
Add chicken.
Brown on all sides.
Remove from skillet.
Add green pepper and onion to skillet.
Stir-fry until softened.
Stir in paprika.
Cook one minute.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add broth (add water if needed).
Add parsley.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove from heat.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Combine "sour cream" and flour.
Stir into hot broth.
Puree small amount at a time in food processor or blender.
Return chicken and sauce to skillet.
Return to heat to warm.
Serve with noodles.
Season with salt and pepper, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 725 calories, fat 19 g (171 cal or 23% of total calories), sat fat 3 g (<5% of total calories), carb 54 g, protein 80 g, chol 250 mg and sodium 670 mg.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk.
Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; combine flour and salt.
Add paste, then flour alternately with buttermilk, vanilla and vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dutch fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut the tomatoes into 1/2-inch thick slices and soak in cold salted water for 1 hour.
Beat egg in small dish.
Mix dry ingredients in another small dish.
Dip tomato slices in beaten egg and then in crumb mixture.
Fry in margarine until lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter; add sugar, beaten eggs, water, soda (sifted with flour), flavoring, nuts and chocolate chips. Roll into balls the size of large walnuts.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: italian casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and drain.
Cook and drain noodles.
Combine all with spaghetti sauce and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 20 minutes.

title: green chile bites
directions: Butter bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Spread green chiles on bottom of pan; sprinkle grated cheese over chiles.
Pour eggs over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until firm when pan is shaken.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve hot on warming tray.
Makes 64 pieces.

title: tomato parmesan salad
directions: In a small bowl or jar with a tight fitting lid, combine oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper; set aside. In a large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients. Chill until ready to serve. Just before serving, whisk or shake dressing; pour over salad, toss.

title: cabbage blender salad
directions: Mix sugar, spices, vinegar and oil and bring to a boil.
Pour over chopped vegetables.
Toss and cool.
Refrigerate.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: creamed ground beef on baked potatoes
directions: Brown onions and beef in fat.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Take from skillet.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Take from heat.
Add milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add meat.
Serve over baked potatoes.

title: chicken dijon #2
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken breasts in butter or margarine until tender, about 20 minutes.
Remove chicken to warm dish. Stir flour into drippings; add chicken broth and light cream.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in mustard. Add chicken, cover and heat 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: hot cheddar bean dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, beans, cheese, chilies and hot pepper sauce.
Spoon into small ovenproof dish.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until cake tests done.

title: five bean casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot.
Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour or several hours in a crock-pot.
Good with ham or at a barbecue.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice onions and boil with vinegar for 3 minutes.
Add sliced cucumbers and spices.
Cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Spices should be placed in bag and tied.)
Ready to can in hot jars.

title: golden carrot jewel cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together the shortening, margarine, sugar, eggs, carrots, orange juice and orange rind.
To this mixture, add flour, Cream of Wheat cereal, baking powder, salt and shredded coconut.
Drop dough by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately and cool on wire rack.
Frost, if desired, with Orange Butter Icing.
Store tightly closed in foil or can.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Add vegetables to marinade and let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Mushrooms or cauliflower may also be used.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need silk flowers, aluminum foil, 2 new clay flowerpots (about 6 inches in diameter) and plastic garden utensils.

title: raggedy robbins
directions: Stir together peanut butter, milk, butter, vanilla, sugar and cocoa or Nestle Quik, then bring to a boil and stir in oatmeal. Time for 1 minute after boiling, then spoon drop (about 1 tablespoon) onto cookie or wax paper.
Will turn into a cookie form after cooling.
Enjoy!

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Spread rhubarb on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, butter and salt.
Add flour, baking powder and milk. Spoon over rhubarb.
Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt; sprinkle over rhubarb mixture.
Pour water evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put biscuits in a Bundt pan in layers around pan.
Heat butter, sugar and cinnamon until butter melts.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for what time it takes to cook biscuits.

title: oven rice
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 475° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir all together while cooking.

title: spiced carrots
directions: In saucepan over low heat, cook all ingredients, except brown sugar, with 3/4 cup water for 15 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Add brown sugar and cook until sugar is completely dissolved.

title: meat balls
directions: Shape into meat balls and place in frypan on medium heat. Brown meatballs, approximately 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove from grease and place in sauce to finish cooking.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Boil pineapple three minutes.
Add lime Jell-O and continue two minutes.
Set aside to cool.
When mixture is completely cool, add prepared whipping cream and cottage cheese.
Nuts may be added, refrigerate.

title: martha washington cherry creams
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir well.
Divide in half.
Put nuts in 1/2 mixture and coconut in other.
Form into balls, a little larger then gumballs.
Place on tray in freezer for 1 hour.
Melt chips with paraffin in double boiler.
Using toothpicks, dip chilled balls into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: tuna and potato skillet dinner
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, combine frozen potatoes and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring often to break up potatoes.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until potatoes are thawed and tender.
Remove cover and stir in garlic, pepper, peas and carrots and tuna.
Cook until peas and carrots are tender and tuna is hot, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in 1 cup cheese mixing well. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Cover and cook over low heat until cheese is melted, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, cheese and 1/2 the butter in large bowl. In glass pan, layer the potato mixture, then noodles, then potato mixture and noodles again until you reach the top.
Pour the other half of the butter over top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take foil off to brown the last 10 minutes.

title: cilantro soup
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil until onions are clear.
Add other ingredients and simmer as long as needed.
For meat lovers, you may add 1 pound hamburger or sausage, browned and drained, to simmering mixture.
Serve with tortilla chips instead of crackers in your bowl.

title: soft pretzels
directions: If using a bread machine, add yeast, flour, sugar, salt and water. After it has gone through first knead cycle, remove dough and divide into 8 equal pieces. Roll each piece into a 12-inch rope and form into
a pretzel shape.
Coat with egg and sprinkle with coarse salt. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Dig one loaf of Hawaiian bread out in the middle to form bowl.

title: lo-cal meat balls
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: clam dip
directions: Rub bowl with garlic; then put garlic on toothpick to put into dip when mixed later. Pour juice off clams and mix with cheese (save clam juice to use if dip is too thick). Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and clams.
Mix well; place garlic bud in center and let set in refrigerator overnight. Next morning, remove garlic bud and stir dip well. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and the melted oleo in bowl; mix by hand.
Spread 1/2 dough in cake pan; bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk in microwave.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over baked crust with melted caramels.
Crumb other half of cake mixture over caramels. Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool until warm.
Cut in squares.

title: yummy chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, chopped apple, nuts, mayo and mustard into food processor.
Blend well.
Serve on crackers or lettuce bowl.

title: cabbage with vinegar(cavolo con aceto)
directions: Trim
bottom
off
cabbage and remove any tough outside leaves.
Slice
cabbage
in
thin
1/8-inch slices.
Clean and slice
onion.
In
large
skillet heat oil and fry bacon until very
crisp.
Remove
from pan and reserve.
Place cabbage and onion
slices
into
hot
oil
and saute until cabbage is well coated
with oil and a little limp.
Add salt and pepper; cook on a medium-low heat until very tender.
Add vinegar and cook an additional 5 minutes.
To serve, crumble reserved bacon and sprinkle on top of cabbage.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marshmallow marble-top fudge
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil; set aside.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons butter with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt marshmallows with 2 tablespoons butter.
Spoon onto fudge.
With table knife or metal spatula, swirl through fudge.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Remove from pan.
Peel off foil; cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: junk salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: turkette
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1 cup cheese.
Sprinkle reserved cheese over top of turkey mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered overnight summer salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust according to package directions for unfilled one crust pie, using a 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 450° for 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: italian tomato sauce
directions: Place tomatoes, half at a time, into blender and process at Puree for 1 minute.
In deep fryer, heat oil and saute onions and garlic in olive oil until soft, but not brown.
Add tomato puree and remaining ingredients.
Turn fryer dial to first medium, then turn to simmer.
Cook sauce uncovered for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If necessary, add a little water as the sauce cooks.

title: pineapple raisin sauce
directions: Simmer together pineapple, 1/2 cup water and the sugar.
Add raisins and simmer longer until raisins are plump (about 5 minutes).
Mix cornstarch and 1/3 cup cold water and add to pineapple raisin mixture along with the few drops of Gravy Master. Stir until mixture comes to a boil. Serve with ham.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar and flour.
In bowl, beat 2 egg yolks with 1 1/4 cups milk; add this to saucepan and mix well. Then add the remaining 1 3/4 cups milk; stir and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup oleo and vanilla.
Stir well and pour into baked pie shell.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Pour into punch bowl the lime sherbet ice cream.
Pour over ice cream one bottle of ginger ale and one bottle of sprite.
Mix frozen limeade as directed on can and add 1/2 of limeade mix to punch bowl mix and 1/2 jar of cherries and cherry juice.
Stir well and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix sugar, mayo and vinegar, then mix all together.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Buy enough yellow summer squash to allow 3 to 4 slices per person.
Remove ends.
Cut squash into 3/4-inch slices.
Shake damp (not wet) slices in a plastic bag containing equal parts sugar and flour until well coated.
Remove to large frypan or electric skillet coated with spray vegetable oil or Crisco.
Do not use butter or margarine.
Saute slowly, turning with care.
Will be soft when cooked.
Parsley if desired.
Delicious.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Cook onions and green peppers until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, tuna, mustard, salt, milk, mayo, mushrooms and noodles.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole at 375° for 20 minutes or microwave for 6 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt together butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once.
Stir.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each until smooth.
Drop by heaping tablespoons, 3 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown and puffy.
Remove from oven and split. Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Spoon prepared pudding into middle of puff.

title: johnnycake
directions: Mix sugar, egg, shortening, sour milk and soda.
Add corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: collard greens(liberian style)
directions: Fry collard greens and onion for about 10 minutes.
Add beef (chicken) and seasoning.
Add 3/4 cup water and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: minnesota cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and peppers
in large bowl and sprinkle salt over all.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for approximately 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Drain completely.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Stir and let stand at room temperature until dissolved.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: pot pie crackers
directions: Combine in large bowl, flour and salt.
Cut in shortening or oleo.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir lightly with fork and form into ball.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each part a little thinner than for pie crust.
Lay rolled out dough on greased cookie sheet. (I roll my dough out on cookie sheet).
Cut into 1/2 to 1-inch squares.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until crackers are lightly browned.
Makes 2 quarts crackers.
Serve with creamed turkey or chicken.
Crackers keep well in tightly covered container and can be made in advance.

title: nut goody bars
directions: Melt in double boiler the chips and peanut butter.
Put 1/2 of mixture in greased pan and chill (9 x 13-inch).
To the other half, add salted peanuts and keep warm in double boiler.
Melt butter; mix in the 1/4 cup of regular vanilla pudding mix and the evaporated milk.
Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over the powdered sugar. Add maple flavoring and mix.
Spread on first layer.
Spread remaining chocolate-peanut mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: basil chicken medley(diabetic exchange)
directions: Heat oil in a skillet, saute garlic.
Add chicken and cook until no longer pink.
Remove and keep warm.
Combine zucchini, tomato, basil and vinegar.
Toss to coat vegetables well.
Add to skillet and stir for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet and heat through.
Serve immediately over rice or pasta. Yield:
4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: About 1 hour before serving, prepare noodles as label directs. Meanwhile, in 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook celery and onion until tender.
Preheat oven to 350°. Into vegetables in saucepan, stir undiluted soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Drain noodles; add, with tuna into saucepan and toss to coat.
Spoon mixture into deep 2-quart casserole.

title: roast and vegetables
directions: Season and flour roast.
In a large Dutch pot, brown roast in oil all over; remove.
Add flour to oil and make gravy.
Add lots of water (will cook down).
Slice potatoes and carrots; add to gravy.
Put roast in.
Add onion (chopped or sliced).
Cook on low to medium heat for about 3 1/2 hours.
Can be cooked in oven at 325° for about 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: sweet and sour wienies
directions: Warm jelly and mustard in saucepan.
Cut wienies in 1-inch pieces.
Drop in sauce.
Put in chafing dish with burner underneath.

title: basic pie shell(diabetic recipe)
directions: Chill shortening.
Cut shortening into flour and salt until mixture forms crumbs.
Add ice water, 1 tablespoon at a time. Flip mixture around in bowl until a ball forms.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill with pie filling, or prick with fork.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until firm, or leave unbaked.

title: girdle busting cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix as directions tell you.
Mix well and press in a long pan that has been floured and greased on the inside. Then mix in bowl the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs; mix well.
Then pour over cake mix.
Add or sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand 24 hours.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: Combine first five ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Let cool completely, then fold in whipping cream.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yield: about 2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender. Cool and remove bones. Cut into small pieces. Save broth. Melt 1 stick butter and mix with cracker crumbs. Pat into bottom of casserole dish, save some for topping. Put chicken on top of cracker crumbs. Spread 1 can Cream of Chicken soup (undiluted) over entire layer. Spread dip on top. Gently pour 1
1/2 cups of broth over this. Top with cracker crumb mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add juice to make 2 cups.
Add to Jell-O.
Add fruits and nuts.
Chill until partially set.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Drop spoonfuls of mixture onto Jell-O, then run knife through and make swirls through mixture. Chill.

title: chicken pie # 2
directions: Boil chicken and dice.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soups and vegetables; pour over chicken.
Do not mix with chicken. Blend well flour, milk and butter until smooth.
Drizzle flour mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Increase heat to 400° for 15 minutes.

title: coconut pie(without crust)
directions: Mix well and pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add all dry ingredients to the corn in a bowl.
Mix well, add egg then butter.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Turn to brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put eggplant in colander; sprinkle with salt and allow to stand 30 minutes.
Rinse well and pat dry.
Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large skillet; saute until lightly browned.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Layer half the eggplant, mushrooms, green peppers, sliced tomatoes, spinach, cheese and chopped tomatoes in greased 5 to 6-quart casserole.
Sprinkle generously with oregano, salt and pepper.
Repeat layering.
Bake uncovered 30 to 40 minutes until veggies are tender.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in a small amount of oil.
Add to drippings celery soup, milk and onion.
Slice peeled potatoes and laye in an 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan (spray pan with cooking spray).
Add layer of cabbage.
Add soup mixture.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered, then 1 hour uncovered, turning pork chops in 30 minutes.

title: fresh green salad
directions: Toss in large bowl.
Serve with dressing.

title: cashew-chex treat
directions: In a large bowl, mix together.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions and celery in shortening; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat about 30 minutes. Makes 2 cups.
Serve with diced or pulled cooked beef or pork.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all together well and serve over lettuce, pretzel salad, etc.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage 1/2-inch thick.
Brown in Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes with liquid, bouillon, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Bring soup to a boil and simmer 1 hour (covered).
Add beans with liquid and cook 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mini pecan rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Blend first 3 ingredients.
Spread in ungreased round cake pan.
Divide the dough into 4 rectangles, pressing perforations to seal.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over rectangles.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of pecans on each rectangle.
Starting at shorter side, roll up each rectangle, pinching edges to seal.
Cut each roll into 4 slices.
Place, cut side down, over brown sugar mixture in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 27 minutes or until light brown.
Cool for 1 minute and invert. Makes approximately 16 rolls.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place mashed sweet potatoes in a mixing bowl; add sugar, syrup, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Beat until well blended.
Add eggs, milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into shell and bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in oil 2 minutes.
Add broth, milk and potatoes. Simmer until potatoes are tender (12 minutes).
Add corn and cook 1 minute.
Puree 1 cup chowder in food processor.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in dry milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Yields 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: pumpkin-spice bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, ginger and cloves. Mix in raisins.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2 inches.
Refrigerate any remaining bars.
Yields 49 cookies.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Process until thick.
Use in your recipe when it calls for sweetened condensed milk.

title: frozen salad
directions: Drain your pineapple and set aside. Mash banana up and then mix all your ingredients up together. Let freeze and then cut.

title: ham-broccoli rolls
directions: Top each ham slice with slice of cheese.
Place half cooked broccoli on each.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt, horseradish mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Combine egg yolk and pineapple juice.
Blend into butter mixture.
Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon sauce over broccoli.
Roll ham and cheese around broccoli.
Secure with wooden pick.
Place rolls in shallow pan.
Cover and bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Spoon hot sauce over ham rolls.
Makes 2 servings.
Can be doubled.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Grind the chicken livers.
Soak the bread in water and then squeeze out the water.

title: sweet and sour chicken salad
directions: In serving bowl, combine chicken, celery, apricot and scallions.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken and stir.
Makes 2 servings.
Contains 226 calories, 11 gm fat and 310 mg sodium.

title: turkey-vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables according to package directions and drain.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with melted margarine.
Press in sheet pan. Mix softened cream cheese, confectioners sugar and beaten eggs together.
Pour over pressed mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown. Immediately remove from pan; cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: may day salad
directions: Whip cottage cheese and jello (prepare per instructions on box) until smooth.
Add fruit; fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until served (at least 2 hours).

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In heavy skillet heat butter.
Season chops with salt and pepper and brown in butter (15 minutes), pouring Worcestershire sauce over chops as they brown.
Remove chops to a deep 10-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and onion salt; spread the onions around chops.
Add drippings left in pan.
Add celery soup. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate-covered raisin clusters
directions: Put chocolate into saucepan over very low heat.
Melt chocolate.
Remove from heat and add raisins or pecans or both. Spoon mixture by teaspoonfuls into tinfoil.
Place in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: jackie's ratatouille
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then top with a little extra Parmesan cheese, parsley and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced pumpkin orange tart
directions: Prepare Crust:
Spray 9-inch fluted pan tart pan with removable bottom with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.
Mix together ingredients with electric mixer on medium.
Stir in hazelnuts; pat dough evenly over bottom and up sides of prepared pan.
Freeze 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake crust for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Blend together in mixer bowl all ingredients except nuts. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pan for 25 minutes; invert on plate and drizzle with glaze.

title: vegetable baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Steam spinach and broccoli until thoroughly thawed.
Pour sauce on the bottom of casserole dish. Spread a layer of cooked ziti, followed by a layer of spinach, a layer of broccoli, sliced Mozzarella and several spoonfuls of Ricotta cheese.
Pour sauce generously over final layer, then repeat layers.
Spread last layer of sauce, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: oriental casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic in oil.
Add celery, soup and mixed vegetables.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Turn into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and top with cheese and almonds.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lo-cal vegetable dip
directions: Three different ways to prepare:

title: fudgy brownie cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pans with paper cups; set aside.
In 1-quart saucepan, heat butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chocolate is melted (5 to 6 minutes).
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: smoked baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onions; add to beans.
Mix together other items and add to beans.
Cover with strips of raw bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan mix the first 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: crabmeat potato boats
directions: Bake potatoes. Cut off tops. Scoop out insides and whip with all ingredients except crabmeat. Fold in crabmeat. Put back in shells. Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. May be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen. If frozen, allow 30 to 45 minutes baking time.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon.
Spread the Miracle Whip over top and sprinkle with sugar and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate (overnight if possible).
Stir well about 15 minutes before serving.

title: beef stew western style
directions: In heavy pan, brown beef in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup mix and water.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables. Cover; cook 20 minutes more.
Gradually blend 1/3 cup additional water into flour until smooth; slowly stir into stew.
Cook; stir until thickened.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend softened cream cheese and 2 Tbsp. of margarine until smooth.
Add the chicken, salt and pepper, milk and pimiento, and mix well.
Open the Quick Crescent Rolls and separate the dough into 4 rectangles.
Put 1/2 c. of the chicken mixture on each rectangle.
Pull the 4 corners of the dough together over the chicken mixture, and twist to seal.
Brush the tops with the remaining 1 Tbsp. of melted margarine.
Sprinkle all with the crushed croutons.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet 20-25 minutes until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, breadcrumbs, milk, onions, salt, Worcestershire sauce and egg together.
Make 1-inch balls.
Cover; cook over medium heat until brown.

title: fresh lemon tartelettes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Place half of each of the ingredients in the bowl and process until smooth.
Mound this batch into a greased loaf pan.
Repeat process with remaining portion of the ingredients and add to the loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until cake is spongy to the touch.
Cool and unmold.
Slice and serve.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, jello, water and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil (can microwave).
Pour into a bowl and chill until thickened. Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into pie shell and chill until set 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with strawberries and trim with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 of butter or margarine with cheese and melt together. Combine with cooked and drained broccoli.
Put mixture in casserole dish and set aside.
Fry crushed crackers in 1/2 butter or margarine until brown.
Layer on top of broccoli-cheese mixture and bake, covered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle Lipton onion soup in buttered casserole.
Over that pour 1 cup uncooked rice (Minute works).
Lay pieces of uncooked chicken over this and pour cream of chicken soup and water.
Bake 2 hours at 325° uncovered in shallow casserole such as 9 x 12-inch or 8 x 15-inch.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with celery and onion. Drain off fat. Mix meat with remaining ingredients. Cover and cook in slow cooker 3-4 hours. Serve on buns.

title: mud pie(basic recipe)
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Mix crumbs with enough melted butter to press into the bottom of a round spring-form pan (a regular pan can be used).
Place in the freezer until firm.
Remove from freeze and fill pan with coffee ice cream, pressing down firmly. Place in freezer again until ice cream is firm.
(This dessert may be made in layers.) Cover with fudge topping (using a warm topping is easier to spread).
Place in freezer to set.
When fudge is hard, cover with whipped topping and serve.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat vanilla, oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Add nuts and apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rave review cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil.
Beat at medium speed.
Stir in pecans.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Bring 5 quarts of water, 3 tablespoons salt and lemon

to a boil in a large saucepan. Add half the shrimp and reduce the heat to medium. Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes. Remove shrimp with a slotted spoon to a bowl of cool water. Bring water back to a boil and repeat with the remaining shrimp. Let cool. In a separate bowl, whisk mayo, mustard, wine, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and dill. Combine with shrimp. Add the red onion and celery. Serve chilled.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Blend in almond extract.
Grease 8-inch tube pan.
Put 1/2 batter in pan. Layer with cranberry sauce.
Layer 1/2 more batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pan after cooling for about 25 minutes.
Ice with 3/4 cup of confectioners sugar, 1/2 teaspoon almond extract and 1 tablespoon warm water.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: hard candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup to 300°.
Remove from heat and add the flavoring and food coloring.
Pour onto a greased pan.
Let stand until cool and break into pieces.

title: no bake chocolate candy cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil; cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Brown potatoes with butter and onion in a skillet.
Sprinkle over the potatoes all the seasonings and herbs. Do this about 1/2 hour.
Add 1/2 cup butter and 1 small onion to the potatoes.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Serves 6 people.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bread can be baked in a sheet pan.

title: strawberry butter delight
directions: Carefully spread peanut butter across one of the pieces of bread, insuring that peanut butter evenly covers entire surface. Take butter knife used and gently wipe peanut butter on second piece of bread to clean knife.
Take teaspoon and dab strawberry jam on second piece of bread.
Then take knife and spread jam across entire surface.
Make sure not to get jam along outside bread edges or crust.
Once jam has been spread, place first piece of bread, peanut butter side down, on top of bread piece with jelly side facing up.
Peanut butter and jam will come in contact with each other causing the two pieces of bread to be held together. Avoid excessive pressure.

title: quick and delicious camp stew
directions: Cook tomatoes, potatoes and onion slowly until potatoes are done.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer on low.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well.

title: chicken cashew for two
directions: Mix 1 teaspoon cornstarch with chicken broth; set aside. Combine 1 tablespoon cornstarch, soy and chicken.
Mix well to coat chicken; set aside.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Peel, cut and cook potatoes until tender.
Place ingredients in casserole dish in layers.
Alternate tuna, potatoes, mushroom soup and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with sharp cheese as desired.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: apricot-ginger barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients until blended.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Great on chicken and fish.

title: imperial pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Slowly add flour until mixture is smooth.
Add walnuts; mix well.
Grease and flour cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Batter also makes 2 lamb cakes.
Top with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: napoleon creams
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar, cocoa and vanilla in the top of a double boiler.
Cook over simmering water until butter melts.
Stir in egg, continue cooking and stirring until mixture is thick, about 3 minutes.
Blend in graham cracker crumbs and coconut.
Press into greased 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate.

title: rotel dip
directions: Melt cheese in saucepan while browning hamburger and sausage in large skillet.
Drain fat.
Combine all ingredients and mix completely.
Serve over nacho chips.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk.
Beat to spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.

title: gibanica(slavic main dish cheese pie)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Follow package directions exactly for working with phyllo dough.
Layer in lightly buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish:
8 buttered pastry sheets, 1/3 cheese mixture, 2 buttered pastry sheets, 1/3 cheese mixture, 2 buttered pastry sheets, 1/3 cheese mixture and 6 to 8 buttered pastry sheets.
Brush top leaf well with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until Gibanica is golden brown and puffed. When slightly cooled, cut into small squares to serve as an appetizer or into large squares to serve as main dish.
Serves 6 as main dish.

title: fried bean cakes
directions: Cook pinto beans in crock-pot until done. Add flour and meal at the same time with the beans and mix together. Add onion, if using. Spoon into skillet with olive oil or shortening. Brown on both sides and serve hot or cold.

title: great cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and peanut butter until blended.
Gradually add both sugars, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Beat baking soda and flour into batter at low speed, until thoroughly blended.
With spoon, stir in chocolate chips. Drop batter from tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets, then lightly flatten each with back of spoon.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cream all the ingredients together; mix thoroughly.
Put in baking dish and cover top with crushed potato chips.
Heat at 350° until bubbly.

title: chili stew
directions: Brown stew meat in a skillet.
Drain and pour into saucepan. Add water.
Let cook for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Add carrots. Let cook for about 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, tomato sauce and chili seasoning.
When this mixture starts boiling, cook for about 25 minutes on medium or until mixture is thick.
Stew should be thick.
Water can be added during cooking time as needed.
Stir often.

title: no-bake peanut butter log
directions: Combine powdered sugar and butter in a large mixing bowl and beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in peanut butter and cereal, mixing with hands if needed.
Shape dough into 1 1/2 x 1-inch logs.
Chill.
Spread tops of cookies with frosting.

title: three bean bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Turn into 2 1/2-quart bean pot or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If you use a crock-pot, cook on high 4 to 6 hours.

title: tiny pecan tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine; blend in flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Press into tiny ungreased muffin tins.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into smaller than bite size pieces. Cut off tough outer layer of the stalks and chop the tender part into small pieces.
You need about 8 cups of broccoli.
In a small skillet, saute the bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Slice the onion lengthwise, then cut into julienne strips.
In a large bowl, combine the broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
In a small bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Combine the dressing with the vegetables and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving, mixing once during this time.
At serving time, stir in the sunflower seeds.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1/2 of cheese.
Place in greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes covered with foil.
Mixture should be bubbly and cheese melted.

title: marcy davis' turtle cake recipe
directions: Prepare German chocolate cake mix.
Pour 1/2 batter in oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hot or cold carob milkshake
directions: Combine in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Heat if desired. Serves 2.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Clean and prepare cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Shred lettuce and mix together with first 2 ingredients. Slice crosswise red onion and let the onion rings fall apart loosely.
Fry bacon real crispy and drain, then crumble over the before things.
Mix honey and mayonnaise well and pour over salad.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix up real well.
This will keep for several days if sealed and put in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry fluff pie
directions: Drain strawberries; set aside syrup and fruit.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add sugar, reserved strawberry syrup and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Prepare whipped topping mix according to package directions.
Fold whipped topping and reserved strawberries into gelatin.
Pour into crust.
Chill several hours until firm.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass or stone bowl and let rise to double
its
size.	Knead
it good and make out into rolls. Let rise and bake.
Never fails!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into crust and bake.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° to finish baking.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cheese, sugar, and peanut butter until very creamy.
Fold in cool whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Garnish with chopped nuts or slivered chocolate.
Chill 6 hours before serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat shortening in a heavy pan and blend in the flour.
Cook over medium-high heat until roux is golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables and cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add water, tomato sauce, dry seasonings and lemon.
Turn heat low; cover pan.
Watch closely and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and heat.
Serve over fluffy rice. Yield:
4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Thin with milk.
Use with fresh pineapple, apples, bananas, grapes, strawberries, etc.
Arrange on leaf lettuce.

title: tex-mex squash chicken casserole
directions: Drain spinach, pressing between paper towels.
Saute squash, bell pepper, onion in hot oil in a large skillet over med. high heat for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in spinach, chicken, next 6 items and 1 1/2 c. cheese.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 X 9 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: caramel cherry graham crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place the graham crackers in a 10x15x1 inch jelly roll pan. Sprinkle the marshmallows over the crackers. Combine the brown sugar, butter, and cinnamon in a small saucepan. Heat until the sugar is dissolved and the butter has melted. Remove from the heat. Stir in the vanilla extract. Pour this mixture over the crackers and marshmallows. Combine the pecans, cherries, and coconut. Sprinkle on top of caramel mixture. Bake for about 5 minutes or until the topping is bubbly and the marshmallows begin to melt. Remove from the oven and place on a rack to cool. Cut into small squares.

title: one pan snack cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry ingredients in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Add liquid ingredients and stir with a fork until completely mixed.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° (apt. oven).
Bake cupcakes at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes (apt. oven).

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt and mayonnaise.
Lightly saute the onions and mushrooms; add soup mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in cheese, shrimp and cooked noodles.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 325°.
Top with Chinese noodles; bake another 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: faye's light lush
directions: Combine cottage cheese and Jell-O, mix.
Drain off as much juice as you can off pineapple and mix with cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Mix in thawed Cool Whip and let sit overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Cover with cold water; let soak overnight.
In the morning, place beans in Dutch oven.
Cover with fresh water.
Cover; cook to boiling point for 30 minutes.
Skim off.
Cut the salt pork into strips and fry until golden brown. Add to beans, along with salt, pepper, mustard, molasses, onion, brown sugar and catsup.
Cover and simmer over low heat, or bake for several hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: greek salad dressing
directions: Mix everything together but olive oil.
Let stand 15 minutes. Gradually add olive oil.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: peaches and cream pie(serves 9 to 10)
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour into pie pan.
Drain peaches (reserving juice) and put on top.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and peach juice; spread on top.
Don't put too close to sides of pan.
Sprinkle on 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Combine the cranberries, orange and sugar; let set overnight. Dissolve gelatin in the hot water.
When gelatin starts to jell, add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into oiled salad mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve on lettuce leaves with mayonnaise.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix in small bowl softened cream cheese, drained crab meat and seafood sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy jam cake
directions: Follow mixing directions on box.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in tube pan as box directions tell.

title: faye's mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix with eggs and oil.
Add oranges, juice and all. Stir carefully.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook required time on cake box.
Cool.
Frost with a mixture of the remaining ingredients.

title: divinity candy
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to a boil, stirring often.
Cook until syrup forms a hard ball in a cup of cold water.
When hard ball stage is reached, pour over beaten egg whites.
Stir until warm.
Add chopped nuts of your choice.
Beat until cool enough to drop on wax paper or greased cookie sheet.

title: barb's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water; add salt and cook until tender, about 45 minutes or more if needed.
Remove chicken from broth to cool.
Strain broth and return broth to cooker.

title: bunis' stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove stem ends.
Remove all seeds.
Place in salt water; cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from water.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly; fill peppers.
Place in baking dish; bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rosarita hearty bean soup
directions: Toss steak in flour to coat.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add steak and cook until lightly browned.
Add onions and peppers. Cook until onions are limp.
Add remaining ingredients except chips and sour cream.
Stir until beans are thoroughly blended. Simmer 20 minutes.
Ladle and top with chips and sour cream.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool for 20 minutes before removing from pan.
Combine brown sugar, butter and 4 tablespoons vanilla in saucepan.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Remove all gristle from meat and season with meat tenderizer and brown in skillet; drain.
In a big soup pot, mix tomatoes, tomato sauce, paste, corn, mixed vegetables, onions, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add meat, cook on medium-low heat for 2 to 3 hours. Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are done.
This makes a lot of soup.

title: power shake
directions: Pour ingredients in blender and process on "blend" until light and frothy.

title: fruit tea punch
directions: Mix sugar and boiling water until sugar dissolves.
Add tea bags to boiling water and steep 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: kitchen bouquet chicken
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish.
Add Kitchen Bouquet. Mix well and cover both sides of chicken with this mixture.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Bake, covered, until tender at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put mushrooms on top and bake with chicken the last 5 minutes.

title: pink snow
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
Place in refrigerator.
When it starts to jell, add well-drained pineapple, marshmallows and pecans.
Chill until jelled.

title: corn and swiss cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 4 (6 ounce) ramekins or custard cups.
Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into cups.
Bake about 25 minutes until lightly browned and puffy.
Garnish, if desired.
Yield:
4. Easy, make ahead dinner party side dish. Great with grilled meat or seafood!

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Drop noodles into boiling water and boil until tender.
Drain. Place small amount of fat in frying pan, add onion and beef and brown together.
Add tomato soup and 1/2 soup can of water.
Let come to a boil; add cheese, stir.
When cheese is melted, add noodles.
Place in greased baking dish and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into thin strips.
Combine with soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Stir and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add beef and stir over high heat until browned.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes on low heat.
Turn heat up and add vegetables.
Stir until tender, but crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan.
Stir until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: microwave chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix all together, using half of the chips in the batter.
The other half goes on top.
Using an 8 or 9-inch square dish, microwave on High for 6 1/2 minutes.
Easy treat for kids.

title: shrimp and noodle casserole
directions: Drop shrimp into boiling salted water.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain well.
Combine noodles with soup, sour cream, onions, green pepper, dried dill weed, pepper and salt. Cut 1/4 of the shrimp into thirds; fold cut shrimp and cheese into noodle mixture.
Spoon into a shallow baking dish.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil; arrange remaining shrimp in rows on top of casserole.
Return to oven for 10 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with tomato slices and fresh dill weed or parsley sprigs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick mexican chicken casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, mix all can goods and stir until well blended.
Stir in crushed corn chips and taco seasoning to taste. Mix well.
Top with shredded cheese and bake in oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees until good and hot.

title: sharon's pound cake
directions: Mix margarine with 1 box of 10x sugar.
Mix well.
Fill box with flour, not quite full.
Add 1 egg and 1/5 of flour to margarine-sugar mix.
Blend well.
Continue to add eggs and flour until well blended.
Add extract and mix well.
Place in ungreased loaf (tube) pan.
Bake starting in cold oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check at 1 hour and thereafter.

title: crab spread
directions: Cream all ingredients together (except almonds) and spread into a shallow baking dish.
Cover with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Spread on crackers.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Mix with corn meal.
Combine egg, milk and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients and stir with fork until moistened.
Bake in greased 9-inch square pan at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: ann lander's meat loaf
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients well; put in loaf pan.
Cover with bacon if you like that flavor.
Pour tomato sauce over all. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Sprinkle in salt.
In large bowl, combine pasta, 3 cups of Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with meat mixture and spaghetti sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: magic chocolate cookie bar
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts; press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 3 by 1 1/2 inch bars.

title: apple bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble together cake mix, brown sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Spread rest of mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together yogurt and egg; pour over apples in pan.
Sprinkle reserved mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese filled manicotti
directions: Brown meats; drain fats.
Add water, tomato paste, onion, mushrooms, oregano, 1 1/2 tablepoons salt, sugar and garlic. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg, parsley and 1/2 tablespoon salt. Cook manicotti in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain. Rinse in cold water; drain.

title: grandfather's special
directions: Brown meat and onion until done. Add other ingredients. Simmer over low heat about 20 minutes or until thick. Serve while hot.

title: strawberry dessert(lucky if you get a piece)
directions: Melt margarine and mix with flour and pecans.
Pat mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat and form into balls.
Fry in 1 tablespoon oil with garlic and onion.
Brown well.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Then add mushroom soup and Parmesan cheese.
Combine with 1 pound cooked spaghetti.
Pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: world's best and easiest cheese ball
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Whip in blender until mixed well.
Pour in dish and put in freezer for 15 to 25 minutes.
Eat your heart out!

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Put in well-buttered baking dish in oven at 350° until knife comes out dry, about 1 hour.

title: cheese and bacon quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Sprinkle the crumbled bacon over the bottom of the tart shell. Combine the eggs, cream, salt, nutmeg and cayenne pepper in a bowl and beat to mix thoroughly. Sprinkle the cheese over the bacon and ladle the mixture over all. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Lower the heat to 350°. Bake for 30 minutes more or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean. Serve in wedges, hot or cold.
(Can add mushrooms and onions cooked in bacon grease.)

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cook pumpkin or sweet potatoes, then mix all other ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.

title: french fried corn
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Remove husks and silks from corn.
Wash and dry thoroughly with paper towels. Cut in 3-inch lengths.
Place 3 to 4 pieces of corn in oil at one time.
Be careful as oil is apt to splatter. Fry until lightly browned, 3 to 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels. Salt.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in top of double boiler. Add water.
Combine egg yolks with juice.
Beat.
Add to rest of mixture and cook until thick over boiling water for 25 minutes. (This does away with starch taste.)
Now add lemon flavoring, butter and vinegar.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into a deep 9-inch baked pie shell and let cool.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: hershey chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for approximately 55 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oreo dessert(yields 12 servings)
directions: Mix together Oreos and butter and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Press firmly and put in freezer.
Spread ice cream (slightly melted) over crust.
Pour chocolate syrup over ice cream.
Return to freezer until ice cream is firm.
Spread 1 (12 ounce) container of thawed Cool Whip over ice cream.
Top with chopped nuts and mini chocolate chips.

title: tomato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and heat.

title: diet sunshine cake
directions: Made with sugar substitute; serve with fruit or sauce.

title: kay's banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and shortening and mix well, by hand or using a mixer. Add the eggs and mix well.
Add the flour, baking soda, salt and nuts and mix well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Test with a toothpick for a clean test.
Remove from oven and cool on a rack for 10 minutes before removing the bread from the pan.
Cool right side up and slice when cool.

title: toasted coconut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix milk, egg, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake 1 hour.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter until soft. Add wine, cumin, cilantro, chili powder and cayenne.
Bring to a simmer then add sausage, beans and tomato sauce.
Return to simmer them reduce heat to low and stir occasionally.
If bean mixture becomes too thick, thin it out sparingly with a little chicken or beef broth.
Serve over white rice.
This recipe makes 4 generous portions but may be halved or multiplied to serve 2 -20.

title: holiday praline delight pie
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar in saucepan with nuts until melted.
Spread in bottom of pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, pepper, salt and oil only over low heat until it comes to a boil.
Pour gently over vegetables and chill overnight.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and sesame oil.
Pierce pork tenderloin with fork.
Place tenderloin in heavy-weight Ziploc plastic bag.
Pour mixture over the meat to coat.
Seal bag. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: kelsie's caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in large heavy saucepan.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over popped corn; mix well.
Put into 2 large deep pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and put in covered container.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Stir until all ingredients are blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots just until tender, drain.

title: baked clams(people who don't like clams like these.)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Fill empty clam shells. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Have the kids collect the shells at the beach and keep a batch on hand.

title: fruit floats
directions: Mix juice with lemon juice and ginger ale.
Fill glasses halfway with liquid mixture.
Drop a scoop of sherbet or ice cream into each glass.
Stir and serve.

title: swedish glogg(beverage)
directions: Wrap herbs in cheesecloth.
Let herbs steep in Port wine, Madeira and sherry a couple of hours in a big pot.
Heat up slowly. Take sugar and place on a rack over the pot with the herbs and wine mixture.
(You can also place the sugar in a metal conical sieve.) Heat cognac in a small pot; pour hot cognac over sugar (light it), then ladle wine mixture over burning sugar until dissolved.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Pour through a strainer.

title: the best baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until half done.
Chop onion. Mix all ingredients together. Put in bean pot or ovenproof dish.
Bake 5 to 6 hours at 250°.

title: greek soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook the beef; drain off fat and remove.
Add the onions.
Cook until translucent and remove.
Add pepper. Cook until tender.
Return onions and ground beef to the pot.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Bring to a boil and lower heat to a simmer; simmer for 20 minutes to cook potatoes.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Cook figs and sugar 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O and cook it in good, then pour into containers.

title: weight watchers sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mash with hands until all Bisquick has been mixed in.
Separate mixture into 16 equal sections.
Each section will make one serving of balls. Form each section into an equal number of balls.
Lightly spray a cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° until light brown. One serving equals 2 Protein, 1/2 Fat and 3/4 Bread.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: On salad plates, arrange spinach, strawberries, oranges and onion.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine the remaining ingredients; shake well.
Drizzle over salad.
Serve immediately.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Remove all green peel and pink flesh from rind. Cut into 1-inch square pieces or smaller if you wish. Combine the 1 gallon of water and salt to make a mild brine; pour over rind pieces and soak overnight. Drain well and cook in clear water for 30 minutes. Drain. Tie cinnamon and cloves in a cheesecloth bag. Combine sugar and 8 cups of water in a kettle. Add lemon, spice bag and boil minutes. Then add rinds, well drained, and cook until transparent. Remove spice bag. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: cream cheese sausage puffs
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until almost done.
Add onions and mushrooms; saute until sausage is no longer pink and onions are tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain and transfer to a mixing bowl.
Stir cream cheese into warm sausage mixture; mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles and cut each triangle in half lengthwise.
Place one teaspoon filling on wide edge of triangle.
Roll wide edge of dough toward the point of the triangle.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 64 puffs.

title: mimosa
directions: Pour the orange juice into a chilled 10 ounce wine glass and fill with champagne.

title: chicken in pastry
directions: Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin; set aside.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender; drain.
Stir in salt.
Roll out each patty shell to 1/8-inch thickness.
Spread 1 heaping tablespoonful of onion mixture on each, leaving a 1/2-inch border.
Place 1 chicken breast half over vegetable mixture.
Moisten edges of pastry with water; roll up, jellyroll fashion.
Place, seam side down, on a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan, pressing edges to seal.
Brush with egg; bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: small applesauce cake
directions: Cream together white sugar, margarine, eggs and applesauce. Slightly flour walnuts and raisins.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Melt the oleo in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients together and place in baking dish on top of the oleo. Top with a little grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Parboil broccoli; drain. Cook rice & mix well with broccoli. Place in 8 X 8 greased pan. Saute butter & onion slices. Add cheese & soup. Mix well. Pour over broccoli & rice mixture. Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Pour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle the yellow cake mix, walnuts and melted butter over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip and slivered walnuts. Then refrigerate.

title: shrimp and chicken divan
directions: Layer 1/3 broccoli, 1/3 mixture of mayonnaise, chicken soup, celery soup, lemon juice and pepper and 1/2 chicken and shrimp mixture.
Repeat twice more.
Refrigerate up to 8 hours.
Bring to room temperature before cooking.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend well.
Mold into loaf and place in a low baking dish.
Dress top of meat loaf with bacon strips and catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together in casserole dish.
Fill almost to top with milk. Cover with two small bags barbecued chips.
Cook at 350° until cheese and butter are melted.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery.
Add everything else and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or cook in kettle on low.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Soak raisins in hot water.
Mix well.
Cut with a large cookie cutter.
Bake at 375°.

title: lemon orange cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in extracts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool for 10 minutes in pans before removing to wire racks to cool completely.

title: sweet and sour dressing for potato salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and break up.
Save grease.
Beat eggs and add rest of ingredients.
Add bacon grease and beat until thick.
If it doesn't thicken, add the cornstarch and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add bacon.
Pour over potato salad mixture.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and add dressing.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla; sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine both previous mixtures and add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake in greased and floured tube pan (10-inch) or fluted for 45 to 55 minutes until center springs back. Cool 25 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.

title: banana and strawberry jello salad
directions: Prepare jello. Add frozen strawberries.
Stir until thawed. Add sliced bananas.
Pour half the mixture in a 9-inch square dish.
Put in freezer until it sets.
Spread a layer of cream cheese and remaining half of the jello mixture and refrigerate until set.

title: sweet surprise
directions: Cut angel food cake in half.
Layer half cake, half pudding and half pie filling.
Alternate layers again.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours.

title: any flavor fudge
directions: In a 6-quart pan, combine sugar and milk.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When heated, add margarine and continue stirring until mixture reaches soft ball (240°). Remove from heat; add bits and marshmallow cream.
Blend well. Stir until slightly thick.
Pour in pan and cool.
Makes 8 pounds of candy.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into well-greased skillet.
Spread the cheese over this evenly. Add remaining mixture over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge and marshmallow candy
directions: Place on top of a double boiler the semi-sweet chocolate bits, condensed milk and margarine.
Cook over medium heat until all is melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan (buttered). Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, oatmeal, flour, soda, salt, pecans, cinnamon, vanilla and raisins. Mix together.
Form into a ball, size of an egg.
Place on cookie sheet with room to spread.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix pecans, flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and oleo.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Fill a 13 x 9-inch pan with broccoli.
Cover with chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and fresh bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks to creamed mixture, then mix in flour, soda and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and mix.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Spoon batter into three layer pans.
(Pans need to be greased and floured.) Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until you can stick the layers with a fork and the fork comes out clean.
Let the cake cool a little before frosting.

title: hot seafood dip
directions: Melt butter; slowly add cream cheese.
Stir until melted. Combine mixture well with a hand mixer or wire whip.
Add crab meat; reheat, adding garlic salt and Tabasco to taste, thinning with milk if necessary.
Serve in a chafing dish with bread cubes.

title: onion appetizers
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Dip in melted butter, then in onion soup mix.
Bake approximately 8 minutes, but watch them.
Serve warm.
Bake at 400°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; add all ingredients and cook.
Serves 4.
You may double recipe and serve 6 to 8 people.
Serve with French bread.
Use brand names for best results.

title: chocolate pound cake
