directions: Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add other ingredients gradually.
Beat thoroughly until well blended.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour batter into greased and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool before removing from pan.
This cake gets moist as it keeps.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Mix Cool Whip, milk and pudding, then mix with cream cheese mixture.
Layer in flowerpot the Oreos and cream cheese mixture, ending with Oreos on top.
Put fake flower in center.
Refrigerate.

title: company chicken
directions: Wrap boneless breasts around ham, Swiss cheese and a few asparagus spears. Place in baking dish. Combine soup, the rest of the asparagus, mushrooms, sour cream, Parmesan cheese and wine. Pour over chicken. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: "philly" cheese bell
directions: Combine cold pack cheese food and softened cream cheese; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into bell shapes, using cold pack containers lined with plastic wrap.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with pimiento strips.
Spread over Nabisco Triscuit wafers.
Yield:
2 bells.

title: chewies
directions: Mix margarine, vanilla and sugar together.
Add eggs, flour and then nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple pie in a jar
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Work until mixture is coarse like meal.
Pour over apple mixture.
Melt butter and pour over mix in pan.
Bake at 350° until brown and crisp.

title: green pepper steak *
directions: Cut beef into paper-thin slices; sprinkle slices with tenderizer according to package directions.
Heat salad oil in large skillet over high heat.
Add beef slices; cook briefly, just until red color disappears.
Add peppers, scallions and celery; cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Blend water with cornstarch; stir in remaining ingredients except rice.
Stir quickly into beef mixture.
Stir constantly until slightly thickened and boiling.
Serve with rice and canned Chinese fried noodles.

title: taverns
directions: Melt in large skillet margarine.
Add ground beef.
Cook until brown, stirring with fork.
Put through food mill.
Add kidney beans and stir well.
Add onion, green pepper, tomato soup, chili sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stir well and cover.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with toasted hamburger rolls. Makes 6 servings.

title: fat-free muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 12-cup muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
In a large bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix fruit, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins and vanilla until well blended.
With spoon, stir flour mixture into fruit mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spoon into pans.
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan. Makes 12.
These freeze well.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger. Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Place a layer of taco shells in bottom of pan, cutting to fit.
Spread 1/3 of the following ingredients over them:
meat, olives, mushrooms and cheese.
Make second and third layers, starting again with the taco shells and ending with cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until meat is hot in center.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares and serve.
A tossed salad goes good with this meal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow sausage to soften to room temperature.
Add biscuit mix, Worcestershire sauce, cheese and enough water to mix.
Shape into small balls and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy gravy
directions: Place chicken on warm platter.
Pour fat from pan into bowl, leaving brown particles in pan.
Return 3 tablespoons fat to pan. Blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.

title: peas and dumplings
directions: Empty peas into medium-size pan.
Add can of water.
Bring to a boil.
Drop in pieces of biscuits, one at a time.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook until dumplings are done, approximately 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line dish with vanilla wafers. Mix vanilla pudding according to directions.
Blend in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 24 hours or overnight.

title: cottage cheese roast
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Smells wonderful while baking.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add water and dill; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 4-5 minutes.
Add milk; stir in lemons and pepper.
Top with fillets.
Cover and simmer for 12-15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup pecans. Shape in ball then roll in rest of pecans.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: panned cabbage
directions: Bring water, bouillon and butter flavoring to a boil.
Add cabbage.
Cover and simmer gently for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften and blend cream cheese and sugar.
Mix together drained pineapple, strawberries, bananas and 1/2 cup nuts and fold in Cool Whip well.
Place mixture into a large glass dish or loaf pan. Freeze solid; slice to serve.
Keep unused portion frozen.

title: salmon appetizer
directions: In medium bowl combine salmon, cream cheese, salsa, parsley and cilantro.
Add cumin if desired.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of salmon mixture on each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla up tightly and wrap individually with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
(Can also be frozen.) Slice each tortilla into bite size pieces.
Yields 48 appetizers.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then turn down to 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: grandma b's chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a small bowl.
In another bowl, mix 1/4 cup cocoa and 3/4 cup brown sugar.
In a small 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, add the first 8 ingredients after they are mixed together. Then pour the second bowl of cocoa and brown sugar mix on top of batter.
Next, pour water over the top.

title: four hour beef stew
directions: Meat may be frozen, no need to thaw.
Place meat into large casserole (5 or 6 quarts).
Place meat in casserole dish.
Place vegetables around it, sliced, and the onion on top.
Sprinkle with sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Pour tomato juice over all. Bake at 250° for 4 hours, covered.
Do not open oven until done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine milk, eggs and cracker crumbs; add meat, mixing well. Shape into a loaf.
Place in baking pan.
Bring to a boil the brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard.
Pour it on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Allow butter and cheese to soften.
Then work butter and cheese together by hand.
Then add the flour, salt, Tabasco sauce and Rice Krispies.
Shape by hand into wafers about the size of a silver dollar.
Bake at 325° on an ungreased cookie sheet for approximately 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sno-cones
directions: Crush ice in blender.
Whirl ice cubes with water until ice is crushed, then pour water off.
Or put ice cubes in an old pillowcase and pound with a hammer to crush them finely.
Then fill a cup 1/2 full of crushed ice.
Pour over a few tablespoons of any kind of juice and stir.

title: tuna cheese log
directions: Mix together cream cheese, tuna fish and onion.
Form into log shape.
Roll in almonds.

title: tuna trio
directions: Mix together.
Shape into balls for appetizers, into croquettes or patties or into a loaf.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes for balls, 20 minutes for croquettes and 30 minutes for loaf.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan well with Pam, sprinkle pecans in pan.
Mix 1st five ingredients on low for 30 seconds.
Then medium for 2 minutes.
On low add sour cream.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.
Cool at least 1 hour before removing from pan (very good).

title: hot dog appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 2 hours.

title: make-your-own-mix
directions: Tip:
Since I have had to limit my salt intake for years, I leave the salt out of this recipe.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Base:
Use cake mix.
Save 1 cup.
Add 1/4 pound melted butter and 1 beaten egg.
Press mixture into bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: slaw with mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in serving dish.

title: black bean soup
directions: Place beans in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with 2-inches water. Soak 6 to 8 hours.
Add
ham bone and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer
covered
about
hours.
Add veggies, salt and pepper and stir to mix.
Simmer covered for 1 hour.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Melt margarine; add peanut butter, then add sugar.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bar.
Spread over top and refrigerate. Cut into squares.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove dark membrane and bones from salmon.
Mix salmon, eggs, onion, cracker crumbs, meal, salt and pepper.
Form into patties and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
May be formed into cone shaped croquettes, rolled in seasoned bread crumbs and baked. You may top with melted cheese or your favorite cheese sauce.

title: cream cheese chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the onion in butter. Add broth, carrots and potatoes. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes until the veggies are tender. Add chicken, parsley, salt and pepper. Combine the flour and milk until smooth. Add to the soup mixture. Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes. Reduce heat. Add cream cheese and cook until the cream cheese is melted.

title: chili casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Cover and cook on auto 5 to 6 hours.

title: freezer jam
directions: Measure 3 cups prepared berries in extra large mixing bowl. Add sugar and mix well.
Let stand for 20 minutes stirring occasionally.
Dissolve the pectin in the water.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add pectin mixture to berries and sugar and stir for 2 minutes.
Pour the jam into freezer containers or freezer jars, leaving 1/2-inch head space at the top.
Cover container and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Store in freezer.
Makes about 7 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Trim crusts and cut Bread in cubes (1 inch).
Melt Cheese and Butter in top of double boiler (over hot water) until like welsh rabbit and add Dry Mustard.
Whisk until smooth; remove from heat; whisk in Egg Whites.
Carefully dip Bread Cubes into cheese with a fondue fork and spread Cheese on sides with butter knife until well coated.
Place on greased cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight. Freeze in brown paper bag.
Bake at 400 for 12 or 15 minutes until puffed and golden brown.
Serve hot.
They melt in your mouth.

title: no bake candy cookies
directions: 1. Boil sugar, milk, butter, and cocoa. One to one and a half minutes after mixture starts to boil, remove from
heat. 2. Add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla, and nuts. Beat
until blended. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
3. Let cool and enjoy !!!

title: four fruit frost
directions: Chill juices.
Mix in sugar.
Add ice cream.
Beat to blend. Pour into 4 glasses.
Garnish each glass with thin slice of orange, lemon and lime with slices touching.
Makes 4 servings.

title: venison barbecue sandwich
directions: Place roast in pan and cover with water.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and boil 1 hour.
Remove roast from pan and flake meat, using fork and knife.
Mix meat with catsup, Worcestershire sauce, corn syrup, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to barbecue mix and cook at low heat 30 minutes, stirring often, until liquid is absorbed.
Serve on buns.

title: asparagus "lovers" pie
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Put in a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (40 minutes if needed).

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add to mixture; beat well. Sift flour 3 times before measuring, then add salt.
Add in small amounts at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured tube pan.

title: best pecan cookies
directions: Mix together butter, 1 cup brown sugar, salt, egg, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Make approximately 1-inch balls and mash out into a small shell with a well in the middle.

title: rice pudding
directions: Simmer on top of the stove until rice is soft, adding extra milk as it cooks down.
(This presimmering is the secret of creaminess.)
Put in baking dish and bake at 325°.
Stir in the brown skin that forms 4 times.
Chill and serve.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Pour all in soup pot.
Let it simmer away for 1/2 to 1 hour. That's it.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mash bananas; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in pans and bake for about 40 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add egg yolks and milk; beat.
Add melted oleo.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook in hot, greased waffle iron.

title: three-minute yogurt pie(slightly sweet, slightly tart-cool-creamy-delicious)
directions: Just fold the tangy taste of your favorite strawberry yogurt into the creamy, fresh taste of Cool Whip.
Spoon into a delicious Johnston's graham cracker crust.
That's it.
Now, your freezer does the rest.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving and place in refrigerator. Garnish with fresh strawberries.
In the unlikely event that any pie is left over, just store in your freezer.

title: fudge(microwave)
directions: Butter a 9-inch square baking dish; set aside.
In a 2-quart casserole or medium mixing bowl, combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter.
Microwave at High for 3 to 4 minutes, or until mixture boils, stirring after every minute.
Reduce to power level 7.
Microwave for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes longer, or until sugar dissolves, stirring 1 or 2 times to prevent boiling over.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until chocolate melts and mixture is blended.
Pour into prepared dish.
Chill to set.
Makes approximately 2 pounds.

title: strawberry sour cream angel cake
directions: Combine 2 cups whipped topping, 1/2 cup sour cream and food coloring.
Mix well.
Fold in strawberries.
Cut angel food cake into 3 layers.
Fill layers with strawberry mixture and cover cake with remaining two cups of whipped topping.
Keep refrigerated. Decorate top with whole berries.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, egg and milk. Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: quick yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix
other
ingredients;
add yeast. Bake in greased loaf pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Mix chicken and 1/2 of grated cheese well.
Add onions.
Open tubes of crescent rolls; stretch dough out.
Place a large tablespoon of chicken mix in center; roll up and seal ends.
Mix the cream of chicken soup and milk in saucepan; heat just enough to spread well.
Cover bottom of baking dish with 1/2 soup mixture.
Place roll-ups in dish, leaving a space between them. Cover with remaining soup.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese 5 minutes before serving.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Make cream sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese, soy sauce, salt and pepper; stir until cheese melts.
Combine rice, chicken, water chestnuts, mushrooms and celery.
Place alternate layers of chicken-rice mixture and sauce mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange noodles around edge of casserole and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter parfaits
directions: Add 2 tablespoons of milk to peanut butter.
Stir in topping. Make pudding.
Alternate layers of pudding and peanut butter mixture.

title: aunt ruth's grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine. Add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Alternate milk and flour mixture into egg, sugar and shortening mixture. Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Do not preheat oven! Spray a tube pan with Baker's Joy and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Yummy on 2nd or 3rd day.

title: swiss hamburger
directions: Fry hamburger patties with onions. Slice green peppers and saute with hamburger and onions.
Drain grease.
Add 1 can whole tomatoes.
Simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk and set aside.
Mix cake mix, margarine, evaporated milk and nuts.
Press half of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Take from oven and sprinkle the chocolate chips on top.
Pour on melted caramels.
Crumble the other half of dough mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: seabolt salsa
directions: Put juice of tomatoes into a blender or food processor set up to chop.
Add onions, garlic, salt and cilantro.
Process until smooth.
Add tomatoes.
Process just slightly.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes; process just until mixed.
Do not overblend.

title: klondike jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Refrigerate until slightly thick.
(I use timer and chill 40 minutes.)
Add mashed Klondikes and fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: To make meatballs, combine all ingredients.
Mixture will be soft.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Place meatballs in a single layer on wax paper-lined cookie sheets.
Freeze until solid.
Store frozen meatballs in freezer bags until ready to cook.
To make sauce, combine all ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved. Place frozen meatballs in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour on the sauce. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 80 meatballs.

title: prime rib roast
directions: Mix seasonings.
Rub well into meat.
Place meat in roasting pan with no cover.
Do not add water.
For well done, bake at 200° for
6 1/2 hours.
For well done on outside and rare inside, bake at 175° for first 3 1/2 hours, then raise to 200° for balance of time.
Meat does not shrink.
Leftover roast wrapped in foil and reheated at 200° will taste just as good.
Slice thin for sandwiches.

title: black-and-white bean salad
directions: Drain the soaked beans and place in separate saucepans.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until tender, 45 to 60 minutes.
Drain beans; rinse under cold water and pat dry.
Combine beans in a large bowl.
Add onion, bell pepper, corn and cilantro (parsley).
Add 2 cups of the Cumin Vinaigrette.
Toss gently to combine.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: fried turkey
directions: Empty the cavity of the turkey and rinse.
Rub the turkey inside and outside with Cajun seasoning.
Drop turkey into hot oil.
Cook 5 minutes per pound. Turkey will float when done. Remove turkey and cover with aluminum foil.
Let oil drain.

title: spinach dip
directions: In covered blender container, blend all ingredients at high speed just until finely chopped.
Cover; refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.
Can be made 1 or 2 days before serving.

title: spaghetti salad(8 servings)
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and cook.
Drain and rinse spaghetti; mix with Italian dressing.
Cool and mix with Salad Supreme.
Add vegetables; mix well.
Place in refrigerator.
Stir every few hours.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy and smooth.
Place one wafer in a cupcake paper.
Pour mixture over wafers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Add and stir in sugar, then flour and baking powder, then warm water and flavoring (teaspoon vanilla).
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350°.
When done, place on waxed paper; spread with jelly and roll.
Refrigerate and slice as needed.

title: napoleon
directions: Put a layer of whole graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Top with icing.

title: peach crisp
directions: Combine peaches, brown sugar, lemon juice, flour and cinnamon in bowl.
Combine cookie mix and coconut in mixing bowl.
Cut in 1/2 cup butter with pastry blender.
Press 1/2 of topping mixture into bottom of 2-quart dish.
Spread peach mixture over crust.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle remaining topping mixture over filling.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add oil and mix.
Add water and mix (may add food coloring with water).
Stir and cook over low heat until thick like play dough.

title: chicken-fried steak
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, sprinkle on both sides of steak.
Combine egg and 2 tablespoons milk in shallow dish.
Dip steaks in egg mixture; dredge in cracker crumbs.
Pour oil to depth of 1/2-inch into large, heavy skillet.
Fry steaks in hot oil over medium heat until brown, turning once.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer, turning occasionally, 15 minutes or until tender. Remove steaks, drain on paper towels.
Keep warm.
Drain off drippings, reserving 3 tablespoons in skillet.
Add 3 tablespoons flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and 1/2 cup milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: mayfield's chili
directions: Boil for 1 hour the ground beef in the water. Add remaining ingredients. Cook 15 minutes. Thicken with 3 tablespoons flour cut into 3 tablespoons shortening. Add 1 quart Campbell's pork and beans.

title: peach cobbler
directions: For biscuit topper, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine milk and egg.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Set aside.

title: arabic coffee qahweh
directions: Bring water to a boil in a brass coffeepot.
Add sugar, then gradually add coffee, stirring until mixture comes to a boil and is frothy. Add cardamom.
Remove pot from the heat until froth has receded, then replace pot on brisk fire.
Repeat 3 times.
Makes 6 demitasses.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook all but liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce and catsup for 20 minutes, uncovered.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Brown meat and onion in large skillet. Add all other ingredients except cheese and tortillas. Heat until it starts to boil. If you need more liquid, add another can of tomato sauce. Tear tortillas in small pieces and spread half of them in bottom of baking dish.
Then add half the meat sauce and spread with half the cheese. Repeat the procedure and place uncovered in oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator chocolate pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread into crust.
Take pie fillings.
Add milk and mix well. Pour into your crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Then grate Hershey candy bar and put on top of pie.
Refrigerate.

title: ham and noodles in casserole
directions: Cook
noodles in salted boiling water until soft.
Pour into colander; drain and wash.
Into a well-greased casserole, put alternate
layers
of noodles and ham.
Beat eggs with the milk and
pour
over noodles and ham.
Set casserole in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine milk, sugar, flour and baking powder and pour over margarine (butter). Do not stir.
Add berries over this and use another 1 cup sugar sprinkled evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: beef-n-cheese crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef, onions and peppers.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and salt.
Simmer while preparing crust.
Separate rolls and place in 10-inch pie plate to form crust; combine egg and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spread over bottom of crust.
Spoon hot meat mixture into crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: delicious fudge pie
directions: Melt and set aside margarine.
Sift together all dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs and vanilla together in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture; mix well.
Add margarine and mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in slow oven at 275° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together the shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rye boat
directions: Mix all ingredients except loaf of bread.
Cut out rye bread center, keeping pieces for dipping on the side.
Fill center with dip.

title: date nut bars
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and mix well.
Combine butter and eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm.
Yields 24 bars.

title: three layer delight
directions: Mix together and press into ungreased pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: pull-apart cinnamon bread
directions: Combine cinnamon and white sugar.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Roll each piece in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Layer pieces into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes before turning out.
Eat warm.

title: t's easy lasagna
directions: Brown
beef and drain.	Add
onion and enough spaghetti sauce to	make
a
little
thinner
than usual.
Cook slowly. Combine grated
Mozzarella with cottage cheese and eggs.
Top with noodles
(place
so
noodles
do
not
touch).
Top with another layer
of sauce, beef and cheeses.	Continue layering until
pan is full.
End with Parmesan sprinkled generously on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting into squares and enjoy!

title: sausage swirls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in oil.
Add milk to make a stiff dough.
Roll dough out thinly on a floured board into 2 (10 x 18-inch) rectangles.
Mix sausages and spread on dough. Roll up lengthwise.
Chill well and slice.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.
May freeze rolls and bake later.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all with Pet milk until desired consistency.
Do not stir. Get shortening hot and drop into grease with spoon.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli (no salt).
Drain well.
Place broccoli in a 10 x 6 1/2-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese. Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and eggs.
Stir well.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, chili sauce and horseradish.
Add shrimp. Just before serving, add celery.
Serves 4.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix together the ground beef and onion soup mix.
Pat down in a large pie plate.
Drain green beans; put on top of beef.
Spread soup on top of beans.
Top with Tater Tots.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
(You can also add shredded Cheddar cheese on top of Tater Tots!)

title: christy's brownies
directions: Mix first three ingredients at medium speed for about one minute, until light.
Add melted butter, beating until thoroughly blended.
Mix in flour and cocoa at low speed.
Stir in nuts. Spread evenly in a greased 8-inch square dish.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn every 2 minutes.
When done, top looks dry and will spring back when lightly touched.
Cut when cool.

title: nutritious rice
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese and onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Great with crackers.

title: chicken, mushroom and noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Saute chopped onion, celery and sliced mushrooms in butter.
Cook noodles and combine with chicken, onion, celery and mushrooms.
Put in casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars and marshmallows over low heat in milk. Let cool in refrigerator to point of being gummy.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Pour into crusts.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Freeze cookie dough.
Slice 1 roll of dough in 1/4-inch slices and layer in an 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg together and mix well with mixer.
Pour mixture on top of sliced cookies.
Slice second roll of cookie dough in 1/4-inch slices and lay on top of cream cheese mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until lightly brown on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat together pudding and milk until slightly thick.
Add Eagle Brand and beat into vanilla pudding mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies, bananas and one-half of pudding two times. Decorate top with cookies.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: pizza, spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt and milk.
Press firmly onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Spoon off drippings.
Combine spaghetti with egg, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Spread in baked meat shell; top with pizza sauce, oregano, pepper rings and cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: cabbage soup(eastern europe)
directions: Combine all ingredients (except lemon juice, sugar and butter) in large soup pot filled with water and cook for 1 hour.
Then add lemon juice, sugar and butter.
Cook for another half hour, adding salt, sugar and lemon juice to taste.
Serve with dollop of sour cream.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes until nearly cooked, but still firm.
Allow to cool, then peel and grate.
Drizzle the melted margarine over the grated potatoes.
In a separate bowl mix remaining ingredients well.
Add to the potatoes.
Place potatoes in a 9-inch square or round baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Beat sugar and peanut butter until creamy.
Add beaten egg. Mix well and add vanilla.
Shape dough into a large ball.
Pinch off pieces.
Shape into 1-inch balls (marble size) and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 2 inches apart.
Press with a fork, making cross marks and flattening.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes until brown.
Let cool before removing from cookie sheet. Results: Crispy cookies.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Combine crackers, salt, pepper and butter.
Sprinkle 1/3 of mixture in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Add layer of oysters. Repeat layers.
Add Worcestershire to milk and pour over top.
Top with crumb mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until browned. Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry slush punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid, jello, and sugar in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple juice.
Cool and freeze in Ziploc bags. About 1/2 hour before serving set out.
At serving time, add ginger ale and chop to mix.
You may use NutraSweet jello and Kool-Aid and leave off sugar for low sugar recipe.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots 5 minutes longer than package directions and drain.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour butter over carrots.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Baste and turn often.
Serves 4.

title: squash jam
directions: Boil squash in water (just barely cover) 6 minutes.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil 6 more minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in jello.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together.
Great with fruit tray.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for approximately 30 minutes or until well browned.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: chili con queso
directions: Fry the onion gently in the butter until it is translucent. Add the tomatoes and chili peppers; simmer, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Add the cheese, stirring as you do.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the cheese melts.
For a thinner dip, add the cream.

title: pesto
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl of a food processor and process until smooth.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Mix all ingredients and turn into greased dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: confederate cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in greased pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: haystacks(fruit and nut cookies with coconut)
directions: Combine egg whites and sugar.
Cook in top of double boiler over simmering water until mixture reaches 120° or feels hot to the touch.
Combine coconut, dates, walnuts, salt and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add hot sugar mixture and blend well.
Mixture will be fairly stiff.
Using small ice cream scoop, form into balls and place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Allow to cool and remove from pan. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: old english apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Place in 3-quart baking dish. Mix sugar, flour and butter together with a pastry blender until coarse and crumbly. Sprinkle crumbs over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: sausage and spinach stuffing
directions: Brown sausage; do not drain.
Melt margarine and add Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper; mix well with a whisk.

title: grilled bacon-cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Mix well and set aside.
Saute mushrooms in 1 teaspoon melted margarine. Drain.
Spread cheese mixture evenly on one side of 4 bread slices, leaving 1/2-inch margarine on edge.
Sprinkle with mushrooms and bacon.
Top with remaining bread and press gently together.
Combine eggs and milk.
Dip sandwiches into egg mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine in a large skillet.
Add 2 sandwiches and cook over medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn sandwiches and repeat.
Drain on paper towels. Repeat with remaining margarine and sandwiches.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer in bowl in order given.
Cover all this with 2 cups mayonnaise mixed with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Set in refrigerator 18 to 24 hours. When ready to serve, top with croutons if desired.
Do not mix. Use a casserole or baking dish or wide bowl.

title: microwave vanilla pudding pie filling
directions: In one 1/2 quart casserole blend together sugar, cornstarch, and salt.
Gradually stir in milk, mixing well.
Microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes until mixture is smooth, thickened and clear.
Stir a small amount of hot pudding quickly in egg yolks.
Return egg mixture to hot pudding, mixing well.
Microwave at Medium High for 1 to 3 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until smooth and thickened.
Add butter and vanilla. Stir until butter is melted.
Pour into serving dishes or prepared pie shell.

title: green jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of boiling water in very large bowl. Cool a little and add Miracle Whip.
Add cottage cheese, milk and fruits, mixing well after each addition.

title: cinnamon bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and let soak for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve 6 to 8.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
After cake has cooled, top with cherries and then top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese pears
directions: Whip cream cheese with honey until smooth.
Set aside.
Place halved pears in casserole dish.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture into the center of each pear half.
Crush graham crackers. Sprinkle over pears.
Drizzle syrup over pears.
Bake in oven on 350° just until top of pears gets light brown.

title: ritz cracker slaw
directions: Grate or chop cabbage; chop onion, celery and bell pepper. Crush crackers.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese. Place grated cheese on top of slaw.
Chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
In a big bowl, mix the cocoa, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Add butter and cheese; mix well.
Put aluminum foil in pan and pour fudge into pan.
Let cool for 1 hour.
Makes 6 1/2 pounds.

title: klondike delight
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Place in refrigerator until almost set. Beat with electric mixer.
Add Klondike bars (one at a time). Blend in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine
ingredients.
For
each
serving add 1 cup hot water to 1/3 cup mix.
Stir until well blended.
Store remaining mix in airtight container.
Makes 28 servings.

title: linda's pizza ole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a skillet, brown the ground beef over medium to high heat; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning and spoon mixture evenly over crust.
Combine eggs, green pepper and onions and pour over meat.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese over this. Spoon salsa on top of this and sprinkle with remaining cheese and chopped tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, slice and enjoy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: better-than-ever-apple-pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Line 9-inch pie plate with bottom pastry crust.
Roll out top crust.
Combine apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Arrange pears in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with apple mixture; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is tender and crust nicely browned. Serve warm or cold.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: low calorie gravy
directions: Add enough water to broth to make 2 cups.
Gradually stir into cornstarch in small bowl until smooth.
Melt butter in small, heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Stir broth cornstarch mixture again; add all at once to saucepan.
Add wine, celery salt and thyme.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Lower heat.
Simmer 1 minute, stirring.
Makes 2 cups.
Calories:
29, fat:
2 gram, sodium:

title: mother's sugar cake with blueberries
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, milk, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in floured blueberries.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: overnight cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and put frozen dough balls into it.
Pour melted butter over dough balls. Sprinkle with pudding, brown sugar, cinnamon, raisins and nuts.
Leave at room temperature overnight. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan shortly after removing from oven.

title: weight watchers barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer, reducing liquid by half.
Makes 1 quart.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Bring to a slow boil, stirring constantly, then let simmer, stirring occasionally until thick.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in skillet.
Add onions and celery and continue to cook for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add undiluted soup.
Blend well.
Pour into buttered casserole (12 x 8-inch).
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: southwestern spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Remove beef and keep warm. In the same skillet, combine the water, tomato sauce, chili powder, garlic powder, salt and cumin. Bring to boil; boil 6 minutes. Add zucchini and spaghetti. Cook 4 to 5 minutes longer or until they are tender. Stir several times. Stir in beef. Sprinkle with cheese. Serve immediately. Makes 5 servings.

title: terry's not-so-sweet homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Note:
Spice amounts are approximate.
I do not measure them. For spicier sauce, add more crushed and ground red pepper.

title: zippy pasta salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bell peppers and onions.
Mix well.
Add dressing and black pepper.
Toss to moisten all ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: mamaliga(a traditional romanian dish everyone will love)
directions: In a 4-quart pot, bring 1 1/2 quarts water to a boil.
Add salt and move the pan off the heat.
Stirring constantly, slowly sprinkle in the cornmeal.
Stir well so there are no lumps.
Return to burner and bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer and let the mush cook slowly for 20 minutes or more.
Stir often.
The final product should be the consistency of thick cake batter.
If it is too thick, stir in a little more water.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift meal, flour, baking powder, salt and garlic salt together in bowl.
Beat egg; add egg and milk to meal mix and stir until well mixed.
Let stand for 5 minutes; add more milk if needed (mixture should be thin enough to drop from spoon).
Drop by small spoonfuls in hot corn oil at 375°.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Melt together over medium low heat, stirring constantly. Serve warm with chips.

title: sourdough bread recipe
directions: In a large bowl, make a stiff batter of ingredients.
Use plastic instead of metal bowls.
Grease another bowl.
Put dough in and turn over to put oiled side up.
Cover lightly with Saran Wrap to set overnight.
(Do not put in refrigerator.)
This dough will raise up a lot so use a very large bowl.
The next morning, punch down and knead a little.
Divide into 2 parts.
Knead each part on a floured board a few times, 8 to 10 times.

title: clay's mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Partially brown meat and drain. Add bell pepper and onion. Saut all until meat is browned and onions are clear. Add seasonings.

title: tanya's cheese dip(for my friends at church, i love you)
directions: Cube cheese; put into large crock-pot on low.
Crumble and brown hamburger; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning (do not add water).
Add to cheese along with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add optional peppers or Tabasco.
Stir occasionally until melted.

title: herbed sour cream mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill sauce and keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together white sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Stir in eggs.
Add chocolate chips and oatmeal.
In separate bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to other ingredients. Drop onto cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix together uncooked rice, soups and water.
Pour into large casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Lay 4 to 6 chicken breast halves on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Uncover and sprinkle dry onion soup mix over top of chicken breasts.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour more.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain salmon and break it apart with fork.
Add eggs, salt and pepper to taste, the onion and just enough flour so that the mixture is not juicy.
Shape into patties and fry in the butter, turning once, until brown on both sides, about 8 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to boil in microwave.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Put in baked pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp marinade
directions: Mix all together and marinate at least 24 hours.
(Cleaning the shrimp is the hardest part.)
Will keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.
For special occasions make a shrimp tree by covering a styrofoam cone with curly lettuce and placing shrimp on it with toothpicks.
Top with a bow.
